WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:01:14.837 --> 00:01:24.671
'Long is this night of sorrows Or long is my mournful song.'

3
00:01:27.055 --> 00:01:32.371
'This wicked night has no end Nor does the flow of my song.'

4
00:01:33.171 --> 00:01:34.231
What say. Shivy?

5
00:01:34.766 --> 00:01:35.558
Sir?

6
00:01:37.148 --> 00:01:40.873
He's a bachelor. sir. He doesn't understand the pain.

7
00:01:41.406 --> 00:01:43.525
Laugh it up while you can.

8
00:01:44.064 --> 00:01:45.650
I’m getting engaged.

9
00:01:46.721 --> 00:01:48.043
This time it’s for real. sir.

10
00:01:50.697 --> 00:01:53.889
Fourth time sir. same story.

11
00:01:54.957 --> 00:01:56.273
Answer me this…

12
00:01:56.544 --> 00:01:59.472
Will you arrive at your wedding on a horse or a police jeep?

13
00:01:59.995 --> 00:02:01.587
A horse of course. sir.

14
00:02:01.855 --> 00:02:03.977
Then what’s the point of being a cop?

15
00:02:04.781 --> 00:02:06.900
Sir. if I show up in a police jeep.

16
00:02:07.165 --> 00:02:09.290
It’ll look like I’ve come to take away a terrorist instead of a bride.

17
00:02:09.555 --> 00:02:11.149
Perfect.

18
00:02:11.416 --> 00:02:14.606
Your bride will stay in line just like a terrorist.

19
00:02:17.799 --> 00:02:18.585
How much longer?

20
00:02:19.389 --> 00:02:22.041
Two more pegs. that's all.

21
00:02:24.706 --> 00:02:25.758
Then make another stiff one.

22
00:02:27.619 --> 00:02:29.743
Where’s your bride-to-be from. anyway?

23
00:02:30.008 --> 00:02:30.804
Dharamshala...

24
00:02:31.601 --> 00:02:32.663
From Himachal.

25
00:02:33.466 --> 00:02:34.792
A purebred Sardarni.

26
00:02:35.060 --> 00:02:37.180
Attaboy!

27
00:02:38.244 --> 00:02:38.774
Sir...

28
00:02:39.046 --> 00:02:40.636
Just mount that horse and show him.

29
00:02:41.172 --> 00:02:47.274
He’ll be digging canals of whiskey from Tarn Taran to Dharamshala for your wedding.

30
00:02:53.918 --> 00:02:55.513
Stop the car.

31
00:03:15.974 --> 00:03:17.559
Come on. step out.

32
00:03:18.091 --> 00:03:20.214
Sir. please. no! Sir. please...

33
00:03:20.483 --> 00:03:21.549
Come on.

34
00:03:22.338 --> 00:03:25.004
Come on! - Please. sir!

35
00:03:26.061 --> 00:03:27.651
Sit! On your knees!

36
00:03:31.109 --> 00:03:31.636
Name?

37
00:03:32.177 --> 00:03:33.230
Nihaal Singh.

38
00:03:34.036 --> 00:03:35.089
Age?

39
00:03:35.627 --> 00:03:36.683
Nineteen.

40
00:03:37.215 --> 00:03:38.274
Village?

41
00:03:39.075 --> 00:03:39.867
Bhikhiwind.

42
00:03:42.000 --> 00:03:43.584
Bhi… Bhikhiwind.

43
00:03:52.063 --> 00:03:52.848
Your name?

44
00:03:54.708 --> 00:03:57.626
Sir. please. let me go. sir. Forgive me. sir.

45
00:03:57.746 --> 00:04:01.180
Get back! Come on! - Quiet! Sit back!

46
00:04:03.976 --> 00:04:05.825
Here… do it.

47
00:04:07.148 --> 00:04:08.205
Me?

48
00:04:09.005 --> 00:04:10.605
No sir. how can I…?

49
00:04:10.725 --> 00:04:12.572
Shut up and do it.

50
00:04:14.042 --> 00:04:16.416
No sir. my job isn’t even permanent yet.

51
00:04:17.482 --> 00:04:20.124
We’ll make you permanent. rookie.

52
00:04:20.388 --> 00:04:21.974
Let's see if you can pull the trigger first.

53
00:04:22.506 --> 00:04:24.894
No sir. I won’t be able to…

54
00:04:25.164 --> 00:04:25.946
No…

55
00:04:26.481 --> 00:04:27.801
Fire the damn gun!

56
00:04:30.457 --> 00:04:31.244
Attaboy!

57
00:04:32.570 --> 00:04:33.362
Go on...

58
00:04:34.173 --> 00:04:36.016
Load them back in the car.

59
00:04:37.602 --> 00:04:39.457
Go on then… get to work.

60
00:04:39.986 --> 00:04:41.045
- Tell me this...

61
00:04:41.165 --> 00:04:43.013
When’s the date?

62
00:04:43.691 --> 00:04:45.541
Haven’t set a date yet. sir.

63
00:04:45.806 --> 00:04:46.870
No? -No. sir.

64
00:04:47.663 --> 00:04:48.726
The thing is…

65
00:04:50.311 --> 00:04:51.895
Sir. the girl has a condition.

66
00:04:53.751 --> 00:04:56.661
She says she won't marry me till I make Inspector.

67
00:04:59.582 --> 00:05:00.898
Bless her.

68
00:05:02.224 --> 00:05:04.607
How many you got left to make Inspector?

69
00:05:06.469 --> 00:05:07.519
Sir. two…

70
00:05:08.053 --> 00:05:09.900
You done? - Yes.

71
00:05:11.494 --> 00:05:12.812
Hold this.

72
00:05:16.787 --> 00:05:21.294
'May I never deviate from doing a good deed'

73
00:05:22.351 --> 00:05:23.147
There!

74
00:05:23.935 --> 00:05:25.260
You're an inspector now.

75
00:05:27.378 --> 00:05:29.231
Get the postmortem done and mount that horse.

76
00:05:33.206 --> 00:05:35.856
'1995. Punjab… '

77
00:05:37.721 --> 00:05:40.086
A north Indian state around the river Satluj.

78
00:05:41.675 --> 00:05:45.118
which has been in a state of insurgency for over ten years.

79
00:05:48.334 --> 00:05:52.833
The constant tension between the police and the militants had exhausted Punjab.

80
00:05:54.952 --> 00:05:57.867
While the police force was trying to eliminate militancy.

81
00:05:58.925 --> 00:06:02.365
a few police officers were taking full advantage of this opportunity.

82
00:06:03.957 --> 00:06:07.129
They stopped distinguishing between militants and civilians.

83
00:06:08.193 --> 00:06:10.573
and the people of Punjab were caught in the crossfire.

84
00:06:12.432 --> 00:06:14.279
The fields had turned barren.

85
00:06:15.883 --> 00:06:18.257
Leaves had dried up.

86
00:06:20.635 --> 00:06:23.284
In this time of terror by uniform.

87
00:06:24.344 --> 00:06:26.459
even rivers had changed their course.

88
00:06:35.203 --> 00:06:37.846
Floating corpses are like floating pages of history.

89
00:06:38.650 --> 00:06:40.228
They never become statistics.

90
00:06:41.028 --> 00:06:42.613
They fill up with water.

91
00:06:43.412 --> 00:06:45.004
They drown...

92
00:06:46.058 --> 00:06:51.086
... taking justice. hope and history down with them.

93
00:07:00.093 --> 00:07:04.595
'Verse chanting'

94
00:07:04.715 --> 00:07:07.092
Very good! And what does it mean?

95
00:07:07.240 --> 00:07:11.743
'O Lord. give me the strength So I may never deviate from doing good deeds.'

96
00:07:11.863 --> 00:07:13.183
Excellent!

97
00:07:16.505 --> 00:07:19.423
Here you go. And distribute them to your friends. Okay?

98
00:07:19.685 --> 00:07:20.743
Kiran!

99
00:07:20.863 --> 00:07:23.507
Coming mummy!

100
00:07:23.920 --> 00:07:25.770
Come on. hurry up.

101
00:07:27.095 --> 00:07:27.889
Give me this.

102
00:07:28.430 --> 00:07:30.280
Let’s go. you’ll get me in trouble too.

103
00:07:30.807 --> 00:07:33.190
Your grandparents are also coming this evening.

104
00:07:33.310 --> 00:07:34.107
Kiran!

105
00:07:34.248 --> 00:07:36.099
We’re here. we’re here.

106
00:07:36.219 --> 00:07:39.132
Hurry up. Kiran! You’ll make everyone late again.

107
00:07:42.719 --> 00:07:44.305
Don’t forget to - - bring the cake.

108
00:07:45.104 --> 00:07:45.630
Let’s go…

109
00:07:45.896 --> 00:07:47.483
Bye. - Bye.

110
00:07:53.845 --> 00:07:55.163
It’s not possible. uncle.

111
00:07:56.224 --> 00:07:58.869
The bank has already loaned you twice against this property.

112
00:07:59.670 --> 00:08:00.722
We're desperate.

113
00:08:02.050 --> 00:08:05.224
Please help us if you can. just this time.

114
00:08:06.552 --> 00:08:08.136
But how will you return these loans?

115
00:08:09.461 --> 00:08:11.315
You could lose your entire home.

116
00:08:11.848 --> 00:08:13.163
We have only one son.

117
00:08:14.492 --> 00:08:15.813
Sukhdev Singh.

118
00:08:16.345 --> 00:08:18.461
He’s been missing for five months.

119
00:08:18.993 --> 00:08:21.379
They say this time he’ll come home.

120
00:08:22.170 --> 00:08:24.827
But aunty… - Please don’t ask anything more. son.

121
00:08:25.614 --> 00:08:26.680
For God’s sake.

122
00:08:27.729 --> 00:08:29.850
We can’t tell you anything.

123
00:08:36.467 --> 00:08:37.533
I’ll try.

124
00:08:43.090 --> 00:08:44.146
Send Mr. Amrik in.

125
00:08:44.414 --> 00:08:45.737
Sir. Mr. Amrik Singh didn’t come in today either.

126
00:08:46.000 --> 00:08:47.365
What? - Yes. sir.

127
00:08:52.812 --> 00:08:54.715
Give this to the head clerk. - Yes. sir.

128
00:08:54.986 --> 00:08:56.895
Tell him I sent you. - Yes. sir.

129
00:08:58.526 --> 00:09:00.157
Please go with him. it’ll be taken care of.

130
00:09:02.617 --> 00:09:04.248
Thank you. son.

131
00:09:05.609 --> 00:09:06.974
Bless you. son.

132
00:09:07.245 --> 00:09:08.331
Bless you.

133
00:09:09.700 --> 00:09:10.509
Hello…

134
00:09:11.056 --> 00:09:13.504
Looks like your parents won’t be coming this evening.

135
00:09:14.603 --> 00:09:15.412
Why. what happened?

136
00:09:15.959 --> 00:09:17.044
No idea.

137
00:09:17.325 --> 00:09:19.497
But he sounded worried.

138
00:09:20.049 --> 00:09:22.220
Could you talk to him?

139
00:09:22.767 --> 00:09:24.126
Okay.

140
00:09:44.284 --> 00:09:47.272
It’s been a week now. Nobody’s seen her.

141
00:09:48.364 --> 00:09:50.002
God knows where she went.

142
00:09:50.272 --> 00:09:52.719
Did you file a police report?

143
00:09:53.818 --> 00:09:55.722
We tried to. son.

144
00:09:56.260 --> 00:09:58.984
But cops don't take anyone’s reports these days.

145
00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:01.977
We scoured the entire village.

146
00:10:02.523 --> 00:10:03.884
but nobody knows anything.

147
00:10:04.429 --> 00:10:07.423
We’ve sent word to the neighbouring villages as well.

148
00:10:07.970 --> 00:10:09.058
Don’t worry. son.

149
00:10:09.332 --> 00:10:11.508
You head home. It’s getting late.

150
00:10:11.781 --> 00:10:14.505
It’s Kiran’s birthday. she’ll be waiting.

151
00:10:15.052 --> 00:10:16.142
Don’t worry.

152
00:10:16.685 --> 00:10:17.775
We’re all here. aren’t we?

153
00:10:18.867 --> 00:10:19.962
Go…

154
00:11:23.136 --> 00:11:24.221
Jassi!

155
00:11:28.307 --> 00:11:30.767
Mindro. open the door!

156
00:11:30.887 --> 00:11:35.506
Aunty? - Jassi! Let me in. son. Open the door!

157
00:11:36.485 --> 00:11:37.293
What happened? - Jassi!

158
00:11:37.570 --> 00:11:39.744
Kirpal never listens to me.

159
00:11:40.024 --> 00:11:42.207
You're his friend. right? You make him understand!

160
00:11:42.327 --> 00:11:45.311
Gurpej... what happened? - Mindro!

161
00:11:45.464 --> 00:11:48.189
Mindro! I've told him so many times...

162
00:11:48.309 --> 00:11:52.116
"Come inside. come inside. You'll catch a cold."

163
00:11:52.544 --> 00:11:53.908
But he doesn't listen.

164
00:11:54.179 --> 00:11:55.275
What happened?

165
00:11:55.540 --> 00:12:00.169
Brother! You come with me. Talk some sense into him. He'll listen to you.

166
00:12:00.724 --> 00:12:02.352
Children these days...

167
00:12:02.895 --> 00:12:05.072
They never listen to anyone!

168
00:12:05.345 --> 00:12:07.794
He'll catch a cold.

169
00:12:08.612 --> 00:12:11.333
He's drenched from head to toe.

170
00:12:11.889 --> 00:12:12.693
Who?

171
00:12:14.333 --> 00:12:17.330
Kirpal! He's lying there in the street!

172
00:12:17.450 --> 00:12:18.532
My Kirpal! - Jassi!

173
00:12:58.449 --> 00:12:59.533
Kirpal!

174
00:13:49.375 --> 00:13:51.013
Jassi. brother? Hello!

175
00:13:51.278 --> 00:13:52.095
Greetings.

176
00:13:52.215 --> 00:13:54.121
Ma... Jassi's here.

177
00:13:55.910 --> 00:13:57.813
Greetings. aunty. - Greetings.

178
00:13:57.933 --> 00:13:59.841
How are you? - Bless you.

179
00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:02.100
It's been a while. Jassi.

180
00:14:02.880 --> 00:14:03.937
I came to meet Satnam.

181
00:14:04.717 --> 00:14:05.510
Is he home?

182
00:14:05.630 --> 00:14:09.564
No… He hasn’t been home since he got his new posting.

183
00:14:09.710 --> 00:14:11.023
It’s been 4 days now.

184
00:14:12.072 --> 00:14:13.645
You tell me... Pammi's fine?

185
00:14:13.765 --> 00:14:14.554
Yes.

186
00:14:14.961 --> 00:14:16.542
Dilbag! - Yes?

187
00:14:16.662 --> 00:14:20.851
Get some water for Jassi. And get him some sweets.

188
00:14:21.262 --> 00:14:22.045
Yes. right away...

189
00:14:22.314 --> 00:14:24.934
Finish this quickly. I’ll be right back.

190
00:14:25.205 --> 00:14:27.037
Dilbag got posted in Chandigarh.

191
00:14:27.313 --> 00:14:28.086
He’s leaving today.

192
00:14:28.882 --> 00:14:30.714
That’s why Jimmy is so upset.

193
00:14:30.985 --> 00:14:32.554
Hasn’t eaten anything since morning.

194
00:14:34.129 --> 00:14:35.964
What’s your business with the police?

195
00:14:37.542 --> 00:14:39.644
It’s… Aunty Gurpej.

196
00:14:40.955 --> 00:14:42.262
You must have heard…

197
00:14:42.531 --> 00:14:43.052
Yes.

198
00:14:44.368 --> 00:14:47.001
I saw her about a week ago...

199
00:14:47.784 --> 00:14:50.407
... serving at the Gurudwara.

200
00:14:51.192 --> 00:14:54.082
Poor woman’s been all alone since Kirpal’s death.

201
00:14:54.608 --> 00:14:57.762
So long as she remembers Kirpal’s no more.

202
00:14:58.023 --> 00:14:59.331
she stays fine.

203
00:14:59.853 --> 00:15:00.908
But when she forgets.

204
00:15:01.446 --> 00:15:04.317
she wanders into police stations looking for him.

205
00:15:06.155 --> 00:15:07.994
She’s lost her bearings. poor thing.

206
00:15:09.313 --> 00:15:10.617
But don’t you worry.

207
00:15:11.145 --> 00:15:12.457
She’ll be back.

208
00:15:12.982 --> 00:15:15.081
Here. have some jaggery.

209
00:15:19.557 --> 00:15:21.910
There's a grimness in the air. son.

210
00:15:22.967 --> 00:15:24.801
Who knows when this season will pass.

211
00:15:37.661 --> 00:15:39.244
Got quite late?

212
00:15:40.818 --> 00:15:41.596
Found out anything?

213
00:15:43.444 --> 00:15:44.492
Not yet.

214
00:15:47.907 --> 00:15:49.478
She was waiting for you.

215
00:15:51.582 --> 00:15:53.149
Wouldn’t even cut the cake.

216
00:15:55.258 --> 00:15:56.565
You’re still up?

217
00:15:57.886 --> 00:16:00.241
Had to prepare a list of books for the library.

218
00:16:00.772 --> 00:16:02.346
Thought I might as well do that.

219
00:16:03.656 --> 00:16:04.705
I’ll take that.

220
00:16:09.969 --> 00:16:11.268
I’ll get you some dinner?

221
00:16:13.379 --> 00:16:14.418
No.

222
00:16:23.609 --> 00:16:24.657
Kids asleep?

223
00:16:24.925 --> 00:16:25.974
They just slept.

224
00:16:49.612 --> 00:16:51.180
Happy birthday. darling.

225
00:17:05.096 --> 00:17:06.401
What's on your mind?

226
00:17:07.465 --> 00:17:08.768
Can't sleep?

227
00:17:12.445 --> 00:17:15.329
I'm thinking what Kirpal would do if he was in my place.

228
00:17:17.170 --> 00:17:20.063
He would also do what you're thinking.

229
00:17:30.831 --> 00:17:33.447
Congratulations. congratulations!

230
00:17:33.711 --> 00:17:36.078
Happy birthday and promotion on the same day.

231
00:17:36.198 --> 00:17:41.179
At this speed. Mr. Inspector will be married by next week.

232
00:17:42.637 --> 00:17:46.578
The DSP's blue eyed boy. his blue eyed boy.

233
00:17:46.698 --> 00:17:48.269
That's enough!

234
00:17:48.680 --> 00:17:50.516
Distribute it to everyone. - Yes sir!

235
00:17:51.567 --> 00:17:52.354
Congratulations. sir.

236
00:17:52.874 --> 00:17:54.976
Go on. have some cake. - Congratulations. sir.

237
00:17:57.610 --> 00:17:58.651
Greetings.

238
00:18:02.851 --> 00:18:03.641
Right...

239
00:18:03.903 --> 00:18:05.742
At your service. - Hello.

240
00:18:08.108 --> 00:18:09.418
We need to file a report.

241
00:18:10.732 --> 00:18:12.829
This is Bibi Gurpej Kaur. from Khalra.

242
00:18:13.097 --> 00:18:14.929
She's been missing for a week.

243
00:18:15.725 --> 00:18:16.505
What's she to you?

244
00:18:17.034 --> 00:18:18.342
She's my friend's mother.

245
00:18:22.279 --> 00:18:23.863
Gurpej Kaur Bannowal.

246
00:18:27.269 --> 00:18:29.110
Kirpal Singh Bannowal's mother. isn't she?

247
00:18:32.006 --> 00:18:33.047
That terrorist's.

248
00:18:34.104 --> 00:18:35.413
A mother's a mother. sir...

249
00:18:36.202 --> 00:18:38.820
Be it a rebel's. or a cop's.

250
00:18:39.879 --> 00:18:41.192
When the crop is bad...

251
00:18:43.284 --> 00:18:45.125
... the rot is in the roots.

252
00:18:46.966 --> 00:18:48.799
Wherever the rot may be...

253
00:18:50.375 --> 00:18:52.210
... it's still the farmer's own farm. isn't it?

254
00:18:54.319 --> 00:18:56.412
Here you go... have some cake.

255
00:18:56.942 --> 00:18:57.990
Go on. have some.

256
00:18:59.306 --> 00:19:00.885
Just file our report. please.

257
00:19:04.296 --> 00:19:05.867
Take some of our cake...

258
00:19:07.706 --> 00:19:09.015
... and we'll take your report.

259
00:19:16.112 --> 00:19:17.166
What’s her name?

260
00:19:17.286 --> 00:19:18.586
Bibi Gurpej Kaur.

261
00:19:19.008 --> 00:19:19.777
And age?

262
00:19:20.582 --> 00:19:21.886
Around 65 or 70.

263
00:19:22.412 --> 00:19:24.766
Village? - Village Khalra.

264
00:19:25.561 --> 00:19:27.656
Sorry… there’s no one by that name.

265
00:19:28.443 --> 00:19:29.763
You were here yesterday as well. right?

266
00:19:31.859 --> 00:19:32.645
Yes.

267
00:19:36.852 --> 00:19:37.371
Excuse me...

268
00:19:38.161 --> 00:19:39.736
Excuse me. are you done?

269
00:19:40.000 --> 00:19:41.101
Yes…

270
00:21:19.440 --> 00:21:21.923
No need for pity.

271
00:21:23.304 --> 00:21:25.240
Nobody cares about them.

272
00:21:26.622 --> 00:21:28.558
All unclaimed bodies.

273
00:21:30.763 --> 00:21:32.147
Let’s go…

274
00:21:35.457 --> 00:21:37.388
If they’re unclaimed. who brought them here?

275
00:21:40.151 --> 00:21:42.086
Not the milkmen. obviously.

276
00:21:44.022 --> 00:21:45.686
It’s no secret who brings them.

277
00:21:46.507 --> 00:21:48.438
but nobody does anything.

278
00:21:49.541 --> 00:21:50.933
Who’re you looking for?

279
00:21:51.207 --> 00:21:52.581
Bibi Gurpej Kaur.

280
00:21:54.236 --> 00:21:55.619
I’ve searched everywhere.

281
00:21:56.175 --> 00:21:57.828
Thought I’d try here as well.

282
00:21:59.217 --> 00:22:00.874
Madam. Are you...

283
00:22:00.994 --> 00:22:01.818
Are you done?

284
00:22:02.255 --> 00:22:03.075
Satnam?

285
00:22:03.633 --> 00:22:04.466
One minute…

286
00:22:07.773 --> 00:22:09.429
She’s not here.

287
00:22:14.680 --> 00:22:16.061
Excuse me.

288
00:22:19.384 --> 00:22:21.311
Ma told me you came home.

289
00:22:22.414 --> 00:22:22.962
All okay?

290
00:22:25.189 --> 00:22:26.553
It’s been ten days.

291
00:22:27.116 --> 00:22:28.775
I’m still looking for her.

292
00:22:30.429 --> 00:22:32.077
If you can help at all…

293
00:22:35.676 --> 00:22:37.329
I’m telling you as a brother…

294
00:22:38.991 --> 00:22:39.812
Forget all this.

295
00:22:40.648 --> 00:22:41.747
Go back home.

296
00:22:42.585 --> 00:22:44.240
You’ve got a wife and kids.

297
00:22:44.517 --> 00:22:45.339
A family.

298
00:22:45.620 --> 00:22:47.550
She’s also family. Satnam.

299
00:22:48.113 --> 00:22:49.763
Kirpal was our friend.

300
00:22:51.141 --> 00:22:53.349
It's my duty to find Aunty.

301
00:22:53.907 --> 00:22:56.668
Then you’re looking in the wrong places.

302
00:22:56.940 --> 00:22:57.498
What?

303
00:22:58.048 --> 00:22:59.155
Sir. sign.

304
00:22:59.438 --> 00:23:00.529
Eight bodies.

305
00:23:03.576 --> 00:23:08.539
No point scraping through ashes. Jassi.

306
00:23:11.028 --> 00:23:12.962
Your own hands get dirty.

307
00:23:14.068 --> 00:23:15.447
Take my advice.

308
00:23:17.381 --> 00:23:18.491
Go back.

309
00:23:19.589 --> 00:23:20.417
Sat -

310
00:23:48.324 --> 00:23:52.735
'TARN TARAN CREMATORIUM'

311
00:24:07.931 --> 00:24:08.754
Yes. tell me…

312
00:24:09.032 --> 00:24:10.135
What do you want?

313
00:24:13.461 --> 00:24:14.837
We’re looking for her.

314
00:24:18.982 --> 00:24:20.639
Earlier. they’d bring 2-3 bodies.

315
00:24:22.018 --> 00:24:23.951
Now it’s 15-20.

316
00:24:24.791 --> 00:24:26.989
Sometimes they bring a truckload.

317
00:24:28.372 --> 00:24:29.471
Can’t say for sure.

318
00:24:39.148 --> 00:24:42.178
Their names. addresses. or any belongings?

319
00:24:43.570 --> 00:24:45.497
We don't get firewood without names.

320
00:24:46.601 --> 00:24:49.914
It takes 400 kilos of firewood to burn one body.

321
00:24:51.026 --> 00:24:54.057
These days most of the bodies are unclaimed.

322
00:24:55.445 --> 00:24:58.206
Every kilo has to be accounted for at the municipality.

323
00:24:59.032 --> 00:25:00.702
Only then we get the firewood.

324
00:25:06.220 --> 00:25:07.314
Where are their names written?

325
00:25:11.464 --> 00:25:13.672
Maybe we'll find something there.

326
00:25:21.680 --> 00:25:23.343
Here you go.

327
00:25:23.893 --> 00:25:26.373
You’ll find all the names in these registers.

328
00:25:28.035 --> 00:25:28.862
And these receipts?

329
00:25:29.150 --> 00:25:31.346
Those are official receipts. from the wood mills…

330
00:25:31.901 --> 00:25:33.001
Where the firewood comes from.

331
00:25:37.145 --> 00:25:39.352
Sometimes. if the bodies pile up...

332
00:25:39.638 --> 00:25:42.126
... we have to burn three on each pyre.

333
00:25:44.058 --> 00:25:45.154
What's the name you mentioned?

334
00:25:46.000 --> 00:25:46.524
Gurpej...

335
00:25:47.328 --> 00:25:48.128
Bibi Gurpej Kaur.

336
00:25:50.544 --> 00:25:53.496
Husband. Darbarilal. Son. Kirpal Singh. Village Khalra…

337
00:25:56.976 --> 00:25:59.384
Here it is... over here.

338
00:26:10.912 --> 00:26:11.978
Unclaimed?

339
00:26:13.594 --> 00:26:14.389
Let it be.

340
00:26:16.539 --> 00:26:17.872
Police encounter...

341
00:26:25.647 --> 00:26:26.986
Jassi?

342
00:26:28.330 --> 00:26:29.125
At this hour?

343
00:26:29.663 --> 00:26:30.732
Went to the police station.

344
00:26:32.346 --> 00:26:33.416
They said you’re home.

345
00:26:37.166 --> 00:26:39.846
I found Bibi’s name at Tarn Taran crematorium.

346
00:26:41.192 --> 00:26:43.067
In a list of unclaimed bodies.

347
00:26:43.863 --> 00:26:45.739
Who is it. Sattu?

348
00:26:46.277 --> 00:26:49.495
No one. ma! It’s Jassi. Be right back.

349
00:26:54.851 --> 00:26:56.723
Your police station is also mentioned in the list.

350
00:26:58.607 --> 00:27:00.212
And your inspector as well.

351
00:27:02.356 --> 00:27:03.959
You were right.

352
00:27:05.306 --> 00:27:06.648
I was searching the wrong places.

353
00:27:09.858 --> 00:27:11.196
You knew everything. didn’t you?

354
00:27:12.276 --> 00:27:13.878
You were there. right?

355
00:27:16.559 --> 00:27:18.161
I’m talking to you. Satnam.

356
00:27:18.970 --> 00:27:19.777
What is all this?

357
00:27:22.720 --> 00:27:25.667
A dark truth written on black paper…

358
00:27:27.287 --> 00:27:29.416
… that can neither be seen.

359
00:27:30.228 --> 00:27:31.561
nor read.

360
00:27:35.580 --> 00:27:36.920
You won’t understand.

361
00:27:38.277 --> 00:27:39.874
That’s why I’ve come to you.

362
00:27:42.820 --> 00:27:44.152
Speak the truth. Satnam.

363
00:27:45.230 --> 00:27:46.563
For Kirpal’s sake.

364
00:27:48.708 --> 00:27:50.318
You’re sitting on holy steps.

365
00:28:00.771 --> 00:28:01.572
That night.

366
00:28:03.186 --> 00:28:04.520
we got a call.

367
00:28:06.669 --> 00:28:08.004
Orders from above.

368
00:28:09.884 --> 00:28:11.226
Where is my Kirpal?

369
00:28:13.368 --> 00:28:15.775
I want Kirpal! - What happened. lady?

370
00:28:16.853 --> 00:28:19.526
I want to meet Kirpal! - Lady… step away from the car.

371
00:28:19.800 --> 00:28:22.471
What happened? - I want to meet Kirpal.

372
00:28:23.012 --> 00:28:24.088
Here. take this.

373
00:28:24.208 --> 00:28:26.619
I’ll give you everything. You keep it.

374
00:28:27.569 --> 00:28:28.637
You keep it.

375
00:28:28.757 --> 00:28:30.632
I want to meet Kirpal.

376
00:28:30.778 --> 00:28:33.994
Lady. listen to me… - Bring my Kirpal...

377
00:28:40.163 --> 00:28:42.031
You know Kirpal. right?

378
00:28:42.307 --> 00:28:44.181
You know where Kirpal is. right?

379
00:28:44.981 --> 00:28:46.590
Where is Kirpal?

380
00:28:46.860 --> 00:28:50.880
Tell me where he is! Where is my Kirpal? - Hey! Lady…

381
00:28:51.000 --> 00:28:56.354
I want my Kirpal!

382
00:29:00.521 --> 00:29:03.477
I want to see Kirpal.

383
00:29:04.812 --> 00:29:06.153
Look at me. mother.

384
00:29:09.101 --> 00:29:10.705
You want to see Kirpal? - Yes.

385
00:29:12.317 --> 00:29:14.192
We're going to go see him right now.

386
00:29:14.992 --> 00:29:16.605
Kirpal? - Yes.

387
00:29:16.725 --> 00:29:18.332
I want to meet him.

388
00:29:18.452 --> 00:29:20.056
You want to meet him?

389
00:29:21.693 --> 00:29:22.495
Satnam!

390
00:29:22.615 --> 00:29:23.686
Yes. sir.

391
00:29:27.048 --> 00:29:28.397
Put mother in the car.

392
00:29:31.343 --> 00:29:32.945
We’ll have a reunion today.

393
00:29:38.306 --> 00:29:42.322
Bless you. son… bless you.

394
00:29:43.396 --> 00:29:45.012
But... but sir…

395
00:29:46.345 --> 00:29:47.147
Son...

396
00:29:47.687 --> 00:29:50.629
I want to meet Kirpal. Let’s go. - Do it!

397
00:29:51.435 --> 00:29:53.577
Hurry up...

398
00:29:54.120 --> 00:29:57.061
I want to meet Kirpal.

399
00:30:00.814 --> 00:30:04.829
Kirpal...

400
00:30:08.318 --> 00:30:10.458
'May I never deviate from doing a good deed'

401
00:30:10.994 --> 00:30:12.065
There!

402
00:30:12.875 --> 00:30:14.487
You're an inspector now.

403
00:30:16.358 --> 00:30:18.497
Get the postmortem done and mount that horse.

404
00:30:21.721 --> 00:30:27.351
'Donate blood while alive; donate your eyes after death'

405
00:30:36.186 --> 00:30:37.789
Greetings. - Hello.

406
00:30:37.909 --> 00:30:38.713
Two bodies.

407
00:30:38.863 --> 00:30:40.210
Killed in a police encounter.

408
00:30:41.008 --> 00:30:41.813
Need their report...

409
00:30:43.696 --> 00:30:44.761
... in 20 minutes.

410
00:30:44.881 --> 00:30:47.018
Give a realistic time for a change.

411
00:30:47.708 --> 00:30:50.653
It takes at least 45 minutes for one postmortem.

412
00:30:51.199 --> 00:30:51.989
Doctor!

413
00:30:52.266 --> 00:30:53.072
What happened?

414
00:30:58.157 --> 00:31:00.034
What's the problem?

415
00:31:00.838 --> 00:31:01.912
There’s just one dead body.

416
00:31:02.714 --> 00:31:03.513
One is alive.

417
00:31:05.393 --> 00:31:06.463
Bloody hell...

418
00:31:08.345 --> 00:31:10.216
Next one ma’am. next one.

419
00:31:12.090 --> 00:31:13.429
Lady. open your eyes.

420
00:31:14.232 --> 00:31:18.250
Lady... lady. open your eyes.

421
00:31:18.796 --> 00:31:21.199
Ma'am... open your eyes.

422
00:31:25.221 --> 00:31:27.096
Get the O.T. ready. - Hold it!

423
00:32:10.770 --> 00:32:11.847
There you go. madam.

424
00:32:12.382 --> 00:32:13.725
Now both are dead.

425
00:32:15.067 --> 00:32:16.396
Twenty minutes?

426
00:32:18.010 --> 00:32:20.150
Bring her out!

427
00:32:25.242 --> 00:32:26.850
I couldn’t do anything.

428
00:32:29.268 --> 00:32:31.136
I couldn’t save her.

429
00:32:37.838 --> 00:32:39.709
Why don’t you quit?

430
00:32:44.537 --> 00:32:46.679
You think I haven’t tried?

431
00:32:49.890 --> 00:32:51.231
I’m not the only one.

432
00:32:51.772 --> 00:32:55.790
There are many cops like me who want to quit.

433
00:32:56.863 --> 00:32:59.814
But for that. we have to sign form 311.

434
00:33:01.955 --> 00:33:03.826
And whoever signs it…

435
00:33:04.365 --> 00:33:06.508
they either disappear...

436
00:33:07.054 --> 00:33:12.133
or they show up dead along with militants.

437
00:33:16.163 --> 00:33:20.174
If I fill up that piece of paper. then you’ll be looking for me next.

438
00:33:23.664 --> 00:33:27.139
When you're riding a lion. Jassi…

439
00:33:29.021 --> 00:33:32.768
When you get off. the lion eats you.

440
00:33:42.684 --> 00:33:44.020
What are you thinking?

441
00:33:46.430 --> 00:33:49.385
There are 600 names along with Bibi's. Pammi.

442
00:33:50.727 --> 00:33:53.668
The list has their families’ names. addresses… everything.

443
00:33:57.148 --> 00:34:00.097
And yet they were marked ‘unclaimed’ and cremated.

444
00:34:01.978 --> 00:34:02.776
Why?

445
00:34:08.137 --> 00:34:10.010
Their families must still be looking for them.

446
00:34:15.914 --> 00:34:17.780
These bodies are not unclaimed. Pammi.

447
00:34:19.935 --> 00:34:20.999
They have families.

448
00:34:22.074 --> 00:34:25.017
And they have every right to know what happened to their own.

449
00:34:28.236 --> 00:34:30.374
I can’t ignore what I’ve seen. Pammi.

450
00:34:33.597 --> 00:34:35.736
Someone needs to speak up for them.

451
00:34:40.839 --> 00:34:42.434
And whoever does.

452
00:34:42.716 --> 00:34:44.315
what about their family?

453
00:34:57.712 --> 00:34:58.783
600 names.

454
00:34:59.327 --> 00:35:01.194
From one crematorium.

455
00:35:02.813 --> 00:35:04.682
So imagine how many in the whole district.

456
00:35:05.749 --> 00:35:07.085
And how many in the whole of Punjab.

457
00:35:07.625 --> 00:35:10.568
These are just the names mentioned in government records.

458
00:35:11.647 --> 00:35:15.669
And those who were drowned in rivers and canals…

459
00:35:15.930 --> 00:35:17.807
There’s no count of them anywhere.

460
00:35:25.853 --> 00:35:27.717
Then get more records.

461
00:35:30.406 --> 00:35:33.885
As many as you can find. wherever you can find them. Get them all.

462
00:35:34.157 --> 00:35:36.035
It is a very sensitive matter.

463
00:35:37.100 --> 00:35:38.973
We have to make our case very strong.

464
00:35:42.995 --> 00:35:44.871
Otherwise there’s no point.

465
00:35:56.393 --> 00:35:57.733
This was probably the first time…

466
00:35:58.807 --> 00:36:03.089
… that cremation records were being unearthed to look for missing people.

467
00:36:04.164 --> 00:36:06.576
Shahida. Jandiala. Durgiana. Patti…

468
00:36:07.647 --> 00:36:10.869
Figures were being collected from all the cremation grounds in the district.

469
00:36:11.667 --> 00:36:16.226
Details of the dead and their killers were being found under layers of ashes...

470
00:36:16.346 --> 00:36:17.409
Here... Amrik Singh.

471
00:36:18.635 --> 00:36:21.309
... which were recorded in the crematorium registers.

472
00:36:21.855 --> 00:36:23.734
but all of them unclaimed.

473
00:36:25.868 --> 00:36:27.480
Jassi. police!

474
00:36:58.566 --> 00:37:00.167
These are unofficial cremation records.

475
00:37:00.700 --> 00:37:02.044
This won’t be enough.

476
00:37:02.317 --> 00:37:03.648
I know it won’t.

477
00:37:04.452 --> 00:37:06.325
That’s why we back these up with government records.

478
00:37:07.129 --> 00:37:10.613
The names of the dead and the cops who killed them are in the municipality files as well.

479
00:37:11.150 --> 00:37:13.027
from where they supplied the firewood.

480
00:37:13.833 --> 00:37:17.053
We tally the municipality records with the cremation records.

481
00:37:19.725 --> 00:37:21.869
Earlier they’d just target rebels.

482
00:37:22.139 --> 00:37:25.085
Now they abduct anyone for extortion.

483
00:37:26.165 --> 00:37:28.836
It's a business... in the name of peace.

484
00:37:32.051 --> 00:37:33.402
It’s a great start.

485
00:37:35.538 --> 00:37:36.607
But it’s not enough.

486
00:37:37.415 --> 00:37:39.025
2097 names.

487
00:37:39.288 --> 00:37:40.633
From just three cremation grounds.

488
00:37:41.163 --> 00:37:43.038
Durgiana. Patti and Tarn Taran.

489
00:37:43.841 --> 00:37:47.325
It still isn’t enough to file a petition?

490
00:37:47.445 --> 00:37:48.787
That’s not the point.

491
00:37:51.616 --> 00:37:52.154
You know him?

492
00:37:52.952 --> 00:37:54.290
Satvinder Singh?

493
00:37:54.564 --> 00:37:56.704
These are all individual cases.

494
00:37:56.976 --> 00:38:00.721
To register them in court. you need to bring their families forward.

495
00:38:01.000 --> 00:38:04.198
They don’t even know that the people they’re looking for are no more.

496
00:38:05.270 --> 00:38:06.872
So it's time to let them know.

497
00:38:07.945 --> 00:38:09.550
You'll have to tell them.

498
00:38:25.869 --> 00:38:28.809
Not all. but many missing people’s names.

499
00:38:29.076 --> 00:38:32.550
their families and where they live. and their police reports.

500
00:38:33.088 --> 00:38:33.891
It’s all in here.

501
00:38:36.565 --> 00:38:37.900
I owe you for this.

502
00:38:38.020 --> 00:38:39.629
For what. Jassi?

503
00:38:40.842 --> 00:38:42.982
You showed me this path.

504
00:38:45.660 --> 00:38:47.794
But what you’re doing…

505
00:38:48.068 --> 00:38:50.740
It’s the work of a true Sikh.

506
00:38:53.677 --> 00:38:55.824
Take care of yourself.

507
00:39:03.046 --> 00:39:05.983
More than 6 months since he left. No news till date.

508
00:39:06.251 --> 00:39:08.928
Is Balli a friend of yours? Do you know where he is?

509
00:39:09.199 --> 00:39:12.133
I was seven years old when I last saw my father.

510
00:39:12.683 --> 00:39:14.809
My mother says he'll be back.

511
00:39:15.081 --> 00:39:16.412
Do you know where is he?

512
00:39:17.487 --> 00:39:19.625
Five years since he left home.

513
00:39:20.161 --> 00:39:23.370
They say he was killed in a police encounter. But I don’t believe it.

514
00:39:24.173 --> 00:39:26.308
They don’t even give any official papers.

515
00:39:26.843 --> 00:39:28.452
That’s his room.

516
00:39:28.572 --> 00:39:30.980
If you know anything. please tell us.

517
00:39:31.396 --> 00:39:33.536
My father was in the police.

518
00:39:34.069 --> 00:39:36.208
Then he left his job.

519
00:39:36.328 --> 00:39:39.536
A few days later. the police came and took him away.

520
00:39:40.229 --> 00:39:41.022
Then?

521
00:39:41.560 --> 00:39:43.964
Then he never came back.

522
00:39:44.765 --> 00:39:46.100
How do I tell them?

523
00:39:47.178 --> 00:39:48.242
Did you see their faces?

524
00:39:50.919 --> 00:39:51.984
It’ll break them.

525
00:39:53.326 --> 00:39:54.394
Get the hell out!

526
00:39:54.670 --> 00:39:55.731
You are a lair!

527
00:39:56.000 --> 00:39:57.759
How do you know he’s dead?

528
00:39:58.062 --> 00:40:00.713
My son is alive! Got it?

529
00:40:01.000 --> 00:40:02.075
He’s not dead!

530
00:40:02.351 --> 00:40:03.959
Mummy! - Get out of here!

531
00:40:04.079 --> 00:40:05.964
Mummy. please come… - You liar!

532
00:40:06.084 --> 00:40:08.768
My son is alive! Mummy. come inside!

533
00:40:09.066 --> 00:40:11.214
Every other day corpses show up.

534
00:40:12.293 --> 00:40:14.709
We're tired of writing to your government.

535
00:40:16.057 --> 00:40:17.939
No one does anything about it.

536
00:40:18.059 --> 00:40:19.410
Another 6 or 7 today.

537
00:40:20.090 --> 00:40:21.970
Clogged up the barrage all night.

538
00:40:22.515 --> 00:40:24.391
Polluted the entire canal.

539
00:40:25.200 --> 00:40:27.616
You expect us to drink this water?

540
00:40:31.115 --> 00:40:33.261
This is a fight for human rights.

541
00:40:33.531 --> 00:40:34.873
For all of us.

542
00:40:35.141 --> 00:40:37.567
This is Navdeep’s fight.

543
00:40:37.832 --> 00:40:39.714
We’ve acquired some government files…

544
00:40:39.834 --> 00:40:43.598
… with detailed records of our deceased brothers.

545
00:40:43.746 --> 00:40:45.899
And we want answers from the government.

546
00:40:46.168 --> 00:40:48.053
That’s why we’re all here.

547
00:40:48.173 --> 00:40:48.715
Yes.

548
00:40:49.390 --> 00:40:51.272
You will go away son…

549
00:40:51.545 --> 00:40:55.038
If the police breaks down our door. how are we supposed to find you?

550
00:41:02.837 --> 00:41:04.991
Here you go. Jaswant Singh. Your cards.

551
00:41:05.111 --> 00:41:06.989
Ten boxes full. Check them.

552
00:41:10.360 --> 00:41:11.168
Okay?

553
00:41:13.321 --> 00:41:13.857
Yes.

554
00:41:14.668 --> 00:41:16.814
If anyone comes. give them this card.

555
00:41:17.625 --> 00:41:19.500
Even to the police.

556
00:41:20.047 --> 00:41:22.729
It has my name. address and number.

557
00:41:22.997 --> 00:41:25.146
You folks have no reason to fear.

558
00:41:25.688 --> 00:41:28.642
Nobody can take away our right to find our loved ones.

559
00:41:29.717 --> 00:41:31.867
And the government will only give answers...

560
00:41:32.143 --> 00:41:34.563
when we come forward and ask for answers.

561
00:41:34.836 --> 00:41:36.171
And demand our right.

562
00:41:36.985 --> 00:41:40.212
Tell us where to go. son. I’ll go with you.

563
00:41:50.689 --> 00:41:52.033
All this is fine. advocate…

564
00:41:53.382 --> 00:41:54.721
But you have no locus-standi.

565
00:41:54.999 --> 00:41:56.879
To file these petitions.

566
00:41:57.143 --> 00:42:00.096
you need to bring all their families to court.

567
00:42:00.645 --> 00:42:03.595
You can’t file the petitions independently.

568
00:42:04.140 --> 00:42:06.017
And all this is meaningless without the families.

569
00:42:07.095 --> 00:42:08.161
Absolutely. your honour.

570
00:42:10.050 --> 00:42:11.927
That’s why we’ve brought the families with us.

571
00:42:15.695 --> 00:42:17.040
That’s it?

572
00:42:18.922 --> 00:42:20.809
Your figures are much higher.

573
00:42:20.929 --> 00:42:23.339
See we had to make a start somewhere so…

574
00:42:24.032 --> 00:42:25.369
You can start with these.

575
00:42:25.640 --> 00:42:29.131
Once the court shows courage. the rest will follow.

576
00:42:51.715 --> 00:42:54.145
What is this human rights issue?

577
00:42:54.945 --> 00:42:57.362
It’s in all the newspapers in New Delhi.

578
00:43:00.053 --> 00:43:03.548
The reputation of the Punjab Police and the government is at stake.

579
00:43:04.623 --> 00:43:07.847
Mr. Bitta… handle it please.

580
00:43:08.120 --> 00:43:09.460
Sir...

581
00:43:10.271 --> 00:43:11.878
Have you followed the Gulf war?

582
00:43:12.425 --> 00:43:14.835
And now the ongoing Chechen war?

583
00:43:15.108 --> 00:43:15.915
Sir do you know…

584
00:43:16.195 --> 00:43:22.365
… how much noise these human rights people make all over the world?

585
00:43:23.176 --> 00:43:26.938
I mean... it's just a gimmick for attention.

586
00:43:27.475 --> 00:43:28.824
Just ignore it. sir.

587
00:43:31.237 --> 00:43:34.468
And who is this Jaswant Singh?

588
00:43:36.623 --> 00:43:38.496
I’ll handle it.

589
00:44:08.879 --> 00:44:09.949
What’re you looking at?

590
00:44:11.840 --> 00:44:13.981
It’s been here all night.

591
00:44:27.423 --> 00:44:28.770
You’ve been here all night.

592
00:44:29.581 --> 00:44:30.920
Must be tired.

593
00:44:32.000 --> 00:44:33.352
It’s tea time. so I brought some.

594
00:44:39.852 --> 00:44:40.938
Just one request…

595
00:44:41.211 --> 00:44:42.836
I have to take the kids to school.

596
00:44:43.105 --> 00:44:45.270
Once you finish. please keep the cups inside.

597
00:45:01.252 --> 00:45:03.428
Sir. greetings.

598
00:45:08.571 --> 00:45:11.548
56 people have surrendered today.

599
00:45:12.902 --> 00:45:15.878
This is neither a victory for us…

600
00:45:16.695 --> 00:45:19.131
… nor is it a loss for the terrorists.

601
00:45:19.950 --> 00:45:23.192
If it’s a loss. it is a loss for all Punjabis.

602
00:45:24.009 --> 00:45:28.070
And if it’s a win. then it’s a win for all Punjabis…

603
00:45:28.341 --> 00:45:32.950
… that peace is finally returning to Punjab.

604
00:45:37.281 --> 00:45:41.881
But there are some people who are unable to digest this peace.

605
00:45:42.705 --> 00:45:46.487
And foremost among them are these human rights people.

606
00:45:47.303 --> 00:45:50.825
Those that they’re calling ‘unclaimed bodies’...

607
00:45:51.095 --> 00:45:56.511
are in reality working in Europe and America as menial workers.

608
00:45:57.062 --> 00:46:01.385
or driving taxis to feed themselves and their families.

609
00:46:02.756 --> 00:46:04.101
And over here.

610
00:46:04.221 --> 00:46:05.848
these human rights people...

611
00:46:05.968 --> 00:46:09.214
... are running their own propaganda against the police.

612
00:46:09.791 --> 00:46:11.142
In reality. these people...

613
00:46:11.958 --> 00:46:14.392
are mere puppets of foreign powers.

614
00:46:15.476 --> 00:46:16.559
And now…

615
00:46:16.828 --> 00:46:20.891
We must protect our Punjab from these people.

616
00:46:21.011 --> 00:46:22.910
If these missing people

617
00:46:23.069 --> 00:46:27.124
have become menial workers in Europe and America. or driving taxis…

618
00:46:27.936 --> 00:46:29.564
Then I’d like to ask Mr. Bitta

619
00:46:29.684 --> 00:46:32.933
why their names are in cremation registers instead of visa files?

620
00:46:33.356 --> 00:46:37.144
Be it the body is of a rebel or a common man.

621
00:46:37.693 --> 00:46:40.131
only their family has a legal claim on it.

622
00:46:40.251 --> 00:46:42.143
Look at these figures.

623
00:46:43.659 --> 00:46:45.551
Patti. Durgiana and Tarn Taran.

624
00:46:45.817 --> 00:46:47.985
From just 3 crematoria in Amritsar district.

625
00:46:48.105 --> 00:46:51.624
we found over 2000 names that were marked ‘unclaimed’.

626
00:46:51.774 --> 00:46:53.400
Including their addresses.

627
00:46:53.944 --> 00:46:55.840
So why weren’t their bodies returned to their families?

628
00:46:56.385 --> 00:47:00.712
And the list also has the names and signatures of the policemen who brought the bodies.

629
00:47:00.985 --> 00:47:05.865
By our estimate. considering all the cremation grounds. this figure it at least 25.000.

630
00:47:06.676 --> 00:47:10.466
And most of them are youths under the age of 30.

631
00:47:13.177 --> 00:47:16.425
This is Nyara Singh and Amrik Singh.

632
00:47:16.696 --> 00:47:18.870
Both were respectable officers in a big bank.

633
00:47:19.139 --> 00:47:20.218
One day they disappeared.

634
00:47:20.769 --> 00:47:24.015
We found out that they too were marked ‘unclaimed’ and cremated.

635
00:47:25.101 --> 00:47:27.261
Have they also fled abroad to become menial workers?

636
00:47:27.534 --> 00:47:31.323
Post emergency the Punjab government has given carte-blanche to the police.

637
00:47:31.870 --> 00:47:33.223
Sikhs are killing Sikhs...

638
00:47:33.494 --> 00:47:35.929
while the people in power are getting rich and fat.

639
00:47:36.476 --> 00:47:38.096
And the state and the courts...

640
00:47:38.216 --> 00:47:40.930
have shut their eyes to the overwhelming evidence in front of them.

641
00:47:41.050 --> 00:47:43.483
That’s why we’ve appealed to international human rights agencies

642
00:47:43.603 --> 00:47:46.583
and the World Sikh Organisation for help.

643
00:47:46.703 --> 00:47:49.136
We are not anti-police or anti-government.

644
00:47:49.256 --> 00:47:52.238
We’re only against those people who. for their own promotions.

645
00:47:52.358 --> 00:47:55.058
have crossed all the boundaries of humanity.

646
00:47:55.714 --> 00:47:58.684
And for this I challenge Mr. Bitta to an open debate.

647
00:47:58.955 --> 00:48:01.123
That he come forward and answer our questions.

648
00:48:20.627 --> 00:48:24.690
The matter on human rights violations is being investigated.

649
00:48:26.046 --> 00:48:31.195
You'll be getting the full report very soon.

650
00:48:32.004 --> 00:48:35.256
Sir. the Rajasthan government has been claiming for some time now

651
00:48:35.376 --> 00:48:38.083
that countless bodies have been flowing in from Punjab’s canals.

652
00:48:38.511 --> 00:48:41.753
And this has been under investigation as well. but no result yet.

653
00:48:42.836 --> 00:48:44.198
Any explanation sir?

654
00:48:45.821 --> 00:48:46.632
The...

655
00:48:47.444 --> 00:48:52.321
bodies being found in Rajasthan are completely unverified.

656
00:48:53.415 --> 00:48:59.362
And accidents happen near the canals all the time.

657
00:49:00.178 --> 00:49:04.243
A lot of people slip and fall in and...

658
00:49:04.792 --> 00:49:06.948
unfortunately they drown.

659
00:49:07.491 --> 00:49:08.845
It’s sad…

660
00:49:09.388 --> 00:49:12.906
It’s tragic but there is no conspiracy.

661
00:49:14.000 --> 00:49:18.275
Bitta sir… there are rumours you’ll be getting another two year extension?

662
00:49:19.348 --> 00:49:22.024
This is a government decision.

663
00:49:22.562 --> 00:49:23.632
And I leave it to them.

664
00:49:23.897 --> 00:49:24.430
Sir...

665
00:49:24.974 --> 00:49:28.183
The open debate that Jaswant Singh has challenged you to…

666
00:49:28.453 --> 00:49:30.327
Would you like to comment on that?

667
00:49:31.128 --> 00:49:32.734
When and where will this debate take place?

668
00:49:33.809 --> 00:49:35.411
Who is he to -

669
00:49:36.755 --> 00:49:37.551
Thank you.

670
00:49:38.627 --> 00:49:40.233
Thank you for coming. - Excuse me. sir!

671
00:49:40.353 --> 00:49:42.493
And thank you everybody.

672
00:49:42.909 --> 00:49:45.854
And yes. please have some snacks before leaving.

673
00:49:46.655 --> 00:49:49.075
Sir you never answered my question. Sir...

674
00:49:49.603 --> 00:49:55.225
I don’t know about your Gulf and Chechen or whatever. but...

675
00:49:55.495 --> 00:49:58.182
Things are definitely getting out of hand here.

676
00:49:58.708 --> 00:49:59.777
You must have seen this.

677
00:50:00.052 --> 00:50:01.928
I need a small favour from you.

678
00:50:02.048 --> 00:50:04.449
Sir. one official picture. please.

679
00:50:07.008 --> 00:50:08.883
Anything to end this mess.

680
00:50:11.560 --> 00:50:14.507
Yesterday you said it would take another week to get out.

681
00:50:15.577 --> 00:50:17.718
What changed overnight?

682
00:50:18.260 --> 00:50:20.394
The DGP will fill you in.

683
00:50:26.021 --> 00:50:27.891
I’m sending you to Tarn Taran.

684
00:50:28.698 --> 00:50:30.037
As Senior Superintendent of Police

685
00:50:30.157 --> 00:50:31.230
Sir.

686
00:50:31.373 --> 00:50:34.321
And you will report only to me.

687
00:50:34.585 --> 00:50:37.530
Sir. I give you my word.

688
00:50:45.029 --> 00:50:46.100
Sir…

689
00:51:00.298 --> 00:51:01.628
Sugga was a loose cannon.

690
00:51:01.893 --> 00:51:04.840
Firing a gun was second nature to him.

691
00:51:05.647 --> 00:51:09.390
As soon as he took charge. abductions. killings and encounters increased.

692
00:51:12.074 --> 00:51:13.941
There was panic everywhere.

693
00:51:15.022 --> 00:51:19.299
An entire generation was being wiped out from Punjab in the name of terrorism.

694
00:51:20.645 --> 00:51:24.388
This bloodshed had been going on for the past ten years.

695
00:51:24.921 --> 00:51:27.604
And the everyone was silent on this whole issue.

696
00:51:28.938 --> 00:51:32.691
The whole issue of human rights violations was being ignored.

697
00:51:36.437 --> 00:51:38.042
Far from trust...

698
00:51:38.577 --> 00:51:40.996
There was fear in the hearts of the people...

699
00:51:41.254 --> 00:51:43.932
which Jaswant Singh and his team fought with all their might.

700
00:51:45.808 --> 00:51:52.232
Punjab Police. answer us! - Answer us!

701
00:51:52.770 --> 00:51:56.520
We demand CBI Inquiry!

702
00:51:56.640 --> 00:52:00.383
Down with Surjit Singh Sugga!

703
00:52:03.746 --> 00:52:04.279
Hello.

704
00:52:06.700 --> 00:52:10.178
Yes hello... it's not too late yet. Talk some sense into him!

705
00:52:10.446 --> 00:52:13.115
Doesn’t he have any concern for his family?

706
00:52:24.366 --> 00:52:25.967
Invitation from Canada.

707
00:52:26.779 --> 00:52:28.385
They've called you on a special permit.

708
00:52:29.987 --> 00:52:31.324
The World Sikh Organisation...

709
00:52:31.444 --> 00:52:35.188
and international human rights agencies want to hear us out.

710
00:52:35.613 --> 00:52:38.553
It’s time to tell the world what’s going on here. Jassi.

711
00:52:39.897 --> 00:52:41.767
This could be our last chance.

712
00:52:42.839 --> 00:52:44.178
Think about it.

713
00:53:08.276 --> 00:53:11.216
Coming to Canada was a crucial step for Jaswant Singh.

714
00:53:12.562 --> 00:53:18.714
This invitation gave Jaswant the chance to present his report on the world's stage.

715
00:53:19.521 --> 00:53:23.537
The Khalsa belongs to God. Victory belongs to God.

716
00:53:24.339 --> 00:53:27.012
I’ve come to this country on a special mission.

717
00:53:28.093 --> 00:53:31.568
to present before you a very important report on human rights.

718
00:53:32.644 --> 00:53:37.456
This report talks about the last ten years of oppression in Punjab.

719
00:53:38.268 --> 00:53:42.543
It talks about thousands of mothers still waiting for their children to return.

720
00:53:43.351 --> 00:53:45.491
Just one question in their eyes.

721
00:53:46.026 --> 00:53:50.315
That someone find out if their children are still in this world.

722
00:53:56.743 --> 00:53:59.679
When we reached the cremation grounds in search of our loved ones.

723
00:53:59.947 --> 00:54:04.498
we found a complete written account of all our lost brothers.

724
00:54:05.307 --> 00:54:08.785
marked ‘unclaimed’ in government registers and cremated.

725
00:54:09.325 --> 00:54:11.467
They say a thief always leaves a clue.

726
00:54:12.000 --> 00:54:13.881
These thieves left so many clues.

727
00:54:14.412 --> 00:54:18.171
that in just 3 cremation grounds in Amritsar - Patti. Durgiana and Tarn Taran.

728
00:54:18.711 --> 00:54:21.663
we found records of 2097 people.

729
00:54:22.198 --> 00:54:24.877
A figure that has since increased to 6017.

730
00:54:25.415 --> 00:54:26.495
According to these numbers.

731
00:54:26.615 --> 00:54:29.838
the number of 'unclaimed’ bodies in all of Punjab is estimated

732
00:54:29.958 --> 00:54:31.560
to be approximately 25.000.

733
00:54:32.670 --> 00:54:34.811
And we appealed to our government as well.

734
00:54:35.357 --> 00:54:37.230
but our words fell on deaf ears.

735
00:54:39.109 --> 00:54:42.864
A mockery has been made of justice. of the law. of an entire community!

736
00:54:43.398 --> 00:54:46.616
And a mockery has been made of all those families who ask nothing more of their government...

737
00:54:47.423 --> 00:54:50.112
than their children’s death certificates.

738
00:54:50.377 --> 00:54:54.400
To those who brand us terrorists and communalists.

739
00:54:55.482 --> 00:54:57.627
I’d like to appeal to them.

740
00:54:58.158 --> 00:54:59.230
People of the world...

741
00:55:00.302 --> 00:55:02.719
those whom you consider the messiahs of peace

742
00:55:03.793 --> 00:55:05.400
and the prophets of democracy...

743
00:55:05.942 --> 00:55:08.890
first recognize their truth. and then tell us...

744
00:55:10.513 --> 00:55:13.454
who is the terrorist and who is the righteous.

745
00:55:27.406 --> 00:55:30.895
The Khalsa belongs to God. Victory belongs to God.

746
00:55:38.942 --> 00:55:40.824
You’ll be taken care of here.

747
00:55:41.636 --> 00:55:44.044
You and your family will be safe.

748
00:55:45.124 --> 00:55:50.484
Thank you. But it’s not just about me or my family.

749
00:55:51.294 --> 00:55:53.705
It’s about thousands of families

750
00:55:53.975 --> 00:55:55.581
who have been betrayed.

751
00:55:55.855 --> 00:55:58.276
and are all living in fear.

752
00:55:58.538 --> 00:56:02.559
I know Jaswant. but I’m serious.

753
00:56:03.639 --> 00:56:05.242
You could get killed back home.

754
00:56:07.662 --> 00:56:10.341
Take the asylum. please!

755
00:56:11.684 --> 00:56:13.033
If I take the asylum.

756
00:56:17.322 --> 00:56:18.663
this mission dies.

757
00:56:24.300 --> 00:56:25.639
Take care of yourself.

758
00:56:28.592 --> 00:56:31.010
Jaswant’s efforts paid off.

759
00:56:32.082 --> 00:56:35.038
The Punjab government was feeling the pressure.

760
00:56:37.712 --> 00:56:43.618
And Amnesty urged the Punjab government to provide Jaswant with extra security.

761
00:56:56.229 --> 00:56:58.376
You’re refusing extra security?

762
00:56:59.184 --> 00:57:01.598
Do you know how special you have to be to get security?

763
00:57:02.681 --> 00:57:04.559
Don’t refuse it. sir. Take it.

764
00:57:14.481 --> 00:57:15.559
You’re his father. right?

765
00:57:16.626 --> 00:57:17.970
Uncle. make him understand.

766
00:57:18.504 --> 00:57:19.847
You’re getting four guys.

767
00:57:20.651 --> 00:57:21.723
Two with him at all times.

768
00:57:21.996 --> 00:57:23.870
And two standing vigilant at the gate. Left - right.

769
00:57:24.684 --> 00:57:28.167
You’ll become a big man at this age. a VIP.

770
00:57:28.702 --> 00:57:31.117
And Mr. Singh is also there. He'll keep stopping by.

771
00:57:32.461 --> 00:57:33.260
Much appreciated.

772
00:57:34.877 --> 00:57:36.216
But if you have to give security.

773
00:57:36.336 --> 00:57:39.288
give it to those families living in fear of the police.

774
00:57:44.535 --> 00:57:45.084
Hello.

775
00:57:45.882 --> 00:57:46.686
Yes. one minute…

776
00:57:48.294 --> 00:57:49.361
MLA Mahinderpal Singh on the line.

777
00:57:55.811 --> 00:57:57.148
Yes. this is Jaswant Singh.

778
00:57:57.691 --> 00:58:00.637
What good is Spring.

779
00:58:00.908 --> 00:58:03.051
if one does not have loving worship of God?

780
00:58:03.329 --> 00:58:06.272
Forgetting the Eternal. our True Friend;

781
00:58:06.540 --> 00:58:08.419
One is engrossed in worldly illusion.

782
00:58:08.690 --> 00:58:11.914
Sons. wives. friends. and wealth shall not go with you;

783
00:58:12.034 --> 00:58:14.174
only the imperishable wealth of the Eternal will go with you.

784
00:58:14.331 --> 00:58:16.736
Those entangled in false affairs are destroyed;

785
00:58:17.008 --> 00:58:18.884
they are lost in the love of duality.

786
00:58:19.155 --> 00:58:24.520
Without the Name of the Divine. nothing is of any use;

787
00:58:24.790 --> 00:58:29.351
There is no Lord except the one Divine.

788
00:58:29.471 --> 00:58:34.570
Those who remain absorbed in the Lord and renounce all. obtain him.

789
00:58:34.727 --> 00:58:37.669
O Nanak. this is my prayer to God:

790
00:58:37.940 --> 00:58:40.619
Please. let me meet the Lord.

791
00:58:40.892 --> 00:58:46.257
I heard about the ripples you made in Canada.

792
00:58:50.553 --> 00:58:52.158
I’m only doing my work.

793
00:58:55.386 --> 00:58:59.407
But going abroad and slandering your own people…

794
00:59:00.489 --> 00:59:01.821
Is that right?

795
00:59:08.000 --> 00:59:12.290
Don’t you think we should keep our problems to ourselves?

796
00:59:12.830 --> 00:59:15.519
We’ve been keeping our problems to ourselves since 1984.

797
00:59:16.596 --> 00:59:18.204
But it's only been getting worse.

798
00:59:19.545 --> 00:59:21.159
Somebody needs to stop this.

799
00:59:23.847 --> 00:59:26.529
You have a small family.

800
00:59:27.883 --> 00:59:31.099
Should anything unfortunate happen tomorrow...

801
00:59:31.645 --> 00:59:33.248
Who will take care of them?

802
00:59:34.872 --> 00:59:38.623
I heard you refused security as well.

803
00:59:39.704 --> 00:59:42.118
You talk about one family.

804
00:59:43.193 --> 00:59:45.076
I’m talking about all those families

805
00:59:45.196 --> 00:59:48.422
whose loved ones were declared ‘unclaimed’.

806
00:59:56.090 --> 00:59:57.975
When an ant bites.

807
00:59:58.774 --> 01:00:00.387
you don’t debate with it.

808
01:00:01.732 --> 01:00:03.089
You stomp it dead.

809
01:00:04.153 --> 01:00:06.573
And you’re no more than an ant to these people.

810
01:00:08.723 --> 01:00:12.478
And what is this rant about 25.000 bodies?

811
01:00:15.436 --> 01:00:19.469
Sugga is just waiting for the order against you.

812
01:00:22.690 --> 01:00:26.721
I’ve kept a prayer at home. I won't lie.

813
01:00:28.331 --> 01:00:30.214
If your skin remains this thick.

814
01:00:31.562 --> 01:00:34.249
then very soon he will get that order.

815
01:00:35.055 --> 01:00:36.392
Understand?

816
01:00:40.962 --> 01:00:42.306
Thank you. goodbye.

817
01:00:51.445 --> 01:00:53.053
Bloody fool!

818
01:01:25.031 --> 01:01:27.173
Why’s Jimmy barking?

819
01:01:27.452 --> 01:01:28.521
You didn’t feed him?

820
01:01:28.792 --> 01:01:29.327
I did.

821
01:01:37.390 --> 01:01:39.273
Saag’s good. isn’t it?

822
01:01:48.676 --> 01:01:49.754
Greetings. mother.

823
01:02:00.496 --> 01:02:02.921
I can sniff out two things from a mile away.

824
01:02:04.530 --> 01:02:06.412
One. a hot plate of saag.

825
01:02:07.484 --> 01:02:09.091
And two. terrorists.

826
01:02:11.515 --> 01:02:12.587
Come. mother…

827
01:02:15.008 --> 01:02:17.154
Feed us some of your delicious saag today.

828
01:02:26.022 --> 01:02:26.835
Greetings.

829
01:02:58.003 --> 01:02:59.335
Exquisite!

830
01:03:01.767 --> 01:03:03.099
Get two more plates.

831
01:03:25.406 --> 01:03:27.287
Start. Come on.

832
01:03:40.464 --> 01:03:41.794
The plates are here.

833
01:03:43.406 --> 01:03:45.018
Brings the guests. - Yes. sir.

834
01:03:51.201 --> 01:03:53.621
Let's go. come on.

835
01:03:57.922 --> 01:04:00.875
Go on. sit. Right there.

836
01:04:01.413 --> 01:04:02.213
Sit down.

837
01:04:12.427 --> 01:04:13.229
You know them?

838
01:04:15.390 --> 01:04:17.271
Yesterday. they were feared militants.

839
01:04:19.418 --> 01:04:20.483
And today...

840
01:04:21.832 --> 01:04:23.978
They betrayed their own people.

841
01:04:27.205 --> 01:04:28.818
And those people tipped us off.

842
01:04:28.938 --> 01:04:30.821
Here. have some.

843
01:04:34.731 --> 01:04:36.068
Now you tell me…

844
01:04:36.608 --> 01:04:38.757
What’s the punishment for being a traitor?

845
01:04:45.477 --> 01:04:46.276
Eat.

846
01:05:14.501 --> 01:05:15.568
Take their plates away. mother.

847
01:05:17.722 --> 01:05:19.872
We shouldn't offend the Gods.

848
01:06:02.594 --> 01:06:05.009
SATNAM!

849
01:06:20.056 --> 01:06:23.813
Rumour has it that someone in the department is leaking inside information.

850
01:06:25.427 --> 01:06:27.040
We're just looking for him.

851
01:06:31.072 --> 01:06:34.027
You know who it is?

852
01:06:48.000 --> 01:06:49.343
I’ll come straight to the point.

853
01:06:52.579 --> 01:06:54.188
I hear Jaswant Singh is a friend of yours.

854
01:06:55.811 --> 01:06:57.692
You grew up together back in Khalra.

855
01:06:59.307 --> 01:07:00.918
When did you see him last?

856
01:07:01.994 --> 01:07:03.338
Remember anything?

857
01:07:07.913 --> 01:07:10.068
His wife’s pregnant.

858
01:07:10.617 --> 01:07:12.763
Her seventh month.

859
01:07:14.374 --> 01:07:15.991
He’s the eldest of the house.

860
01:07:17.337 --> 01:07:18.678
Please forgive him.

861
01:07:19.490 --> 01:07:21.100
Forgive him.

862
01:07:22.717 --> 01:07:24.875
For God’s sake.

863
01:07:25.953 --> 01:07:27.832
Forgive my son.

864
01:07:28.917 --> 01:07:30.523
He hasn’t done anything.

865
01:07:31.064 --> 01:07:34.025
Forgive my son. forgive him.

866
01:07:34.568 --> 01:07:35.640
Look…

867
01:07:36.180 --> 01:07:38.596
Look. I’m begging you.

868
01:07:38.865 --> 01:07:41.556
I’m begging you. please…

869
01:07:41.676 --> 01:07:43.022
Forgive him.

870
01:07:43.443 --> 01:07:45.598
Alright. mother.

871
01:07:46.402 --> 01:07:47.748
Let’s play a game.

872
01:07:48.827 --> 01:07:52.052
If it lands in my right hand. then it’s our luck.

873
01:07:54.752 --> 01:07:56.633
And if it lands in my left. then it’s his.

874
01:08:01.478 --> 01:08:05.237
Eeni meeni miney mo…

875
01:08:06.049 --> 01:08:09.549
Catch a traitor by his toe…

876
01:08:10.088 --> 01:08:14.121
If he squeals. let him know...

877
01:08:14.930 --> 01:08:19.234
Straight to hell. he will go.

878
01:08:22.196 --> 01:08:27.039
Thank God!

879
01:08:28.927 --> 01:08:30.806
What a fortunate son. mother.

880
01:08:33.502 --> 01:08:34.305
Thank you.

881
01:08:42.926 --> 01:08:45.607
Even if I forgive you for betraying your own…

882
01:08:49.111 --> 01:08:49.913
But these...

883
01:08:51.800 --> 01:08:53.411
terrorists that were found in your home.

884
01:08:54.489 --> 01:08:55.568
What about them?

885
01:09:01.489 --> 01:09:02.835
That’s betraying your country.

886
01:09:05.254 --> 01:09:06.063
Right?

887
01:09:14.680 --> 01:09:16.827
That deserves punishment. mother.

888
01:09:44.547 --> 01:09:45.894
Good thing we found out in time.

889
01:09:46.432 --> 01:09:48.854
Or things would have gotten out of hand.

890
01:09:49.660 --> 01:09:52.082
We found out around 9-9:30 last night.

891
01:09:52.625 --> 01:09:54.506
We found these weapons. sir.

892
01:09:56.392 --> 01:09:59.346
Were they going to blow up the whole village with this arsenal?

893
01:09:59.622 --> 01:10:01.771
Who knows what they were up to.

894
01:10:03.388 --> 01:10:05.814
Do an inventory of these weapons. - Yes. sir.

895
01:10:06.349 --> 01:10:09.034
Then get witness testimonies and send these bodies for postmortem.

896
01:10:10.651 --> 01:10:13.354
3 AK-47s. - Yes sir.

897
01:10:13.613 --> 01:10:15.765
2 Carbines. - Yes sir.

898
01:10:16.303 --> 01:10:17.651
5 Mausers.

899
01:10:17.922 --> 01:10:19.533
Yes sir.

900
01:11:45.926 --> 01:11:47.808
What are you doing this late?

901
01:11:49.698 --> 01:11:51.041
I'm sleeping here from tonight.

902
01:11:52.117 --> 01:11:55.079
If they come. they'll find me first.

903
01:11:59.652 --> 01:12:02.076
At least they won’t get to you and the kids.

904
01:12:07.184 --> 01:12:10.412
First time I’m seeing you this scared.

905
01:12:13.376 --> 01:12:15.526
I'm not scared for myself. Pammi.

906
01:12:18.491 --> 01:12:19.835
You asked me. didn’t you…

907
01:12:20.646 --> 01:12:22.535
Whoever steps up. what about their family?

908
01:12:25.214 --> 01:12:27.641
This decision is for my family.

909
01:12:32.219 --> 01:12:34.096
I’ve come too far. Pammi.

910
01:12:37.332 --> 01:12:39.749
It’s been three months since we filed our petition.

911
01:12:40.561 --> 01:12:42.168
But still no answers.

912
01:12:43.247 --> 01:12:47.018
And in response. my family and I are being threatened.

913
01:12:48.371 --> 01:12:49.711
We’re being watched.

914
01:12:50.514 --> 01:12:53.751
But I’d like to let them know that their threats won’t work.

915
01:12:54.551 --> 01:12:56.435
If something happens to me tomorrow…

916
01:12:56.704 --> 01:12:58.588
If a car or a truck runs me over.

917
01:12:59.132 --> 01:13:02.353
if I get shot. or if you find my body floating in some canal...

918
01:13:03.168 --> 01:13:05.587
then no single cop will be to blame.

919
01:13:06.125 --> 01:13:09.353
The blame will fall on the Punjab government and DGP Bitta.

920
01:13:10.436 --> 01:13:13.390
who have given free reign to men like SSP Sugga.

921
01:13:16.356 --> 01:13:17.701
Hey. calm down.

922
01:13:18.505 --> 01:13:19.850
We are at war.

923
01:13:20.392 --> 01:13:24.429
We’ve been fighting a low-intensity proxy war for the last ten years.

924
01:13:25.506 --> 01:13:30.618
While it is every citizen's democratic right to ask questions.

925
01:13:31.152 --> 01:13:33.305
you must also remember.

926
01:13:33.425 --> 01:13:37.732
it is because of us that you have that right.

927
01:13:38.162 --> 01:13:41.379
Or else Punjab would have become a militant state a long time ago.

928
01:13:43.268 --> 01:13:44.607
You see...

929
01:13:44.880 --> 01:13:47.033
War and peace

930
01:13:47.311 --> 01:13:50.528
are two sides of the same coin.

931
01:13:51.076 --> 01:14:04.256
'The Divine Truth'

932
01:14:05.611 --> 01:14:12.060
leads me to the Light.

933
01:14:13.407 --> 01:14:21.480
The battle drum beats in my mind’s sky

934
01:14:22.022 --> 01:14:28.481
Aim is taken and the wound is inflicted.

935
01:14:29.284 --> 01:14:39.510
The spiritual warriors enter the field of battle.

936
01:14:40.862 --> 01:14:49.738
Now is the time to fight.

937
01:14:50.814 --> 01:14:56.734
He alone is known as a spiritual warrior

938
01:14:57.550 --> 01:15:03.464
who fights in defense of his faith.

939
01:15:10.467 --> 01:15:13.691
Piece by piece.

940
01:15:14.233 --> 01:15:18.265
he is cut apart.

941
01:15:19.075 --> 01:15:21.765
We have just learned that at approximately 9:30 this morning.

942
01:15:21.885 --> 01:15:25.919
CM Anant Singh was killed in an explosion at the Chandigarh secretariat.

943
01:15:26.077 --> 01:15:30.110
CM Anant Singh’s assassin. Dilbag Singh. was a member of the CM’s own security detail.

944
01:15:30.230 --> 01:15:36.957
But he never leaves the field of battle.

945
01:15:40.604 --> 01:15:43.293
17 people were blown to shreds in the blast.

946
01:15:44.376 --> 01:15:47.339
Nobody knew who was burning in the casket.

947
01:15:48.949 --> 01:15:52.442
And this entire mess was being seen as DGP Bitta’s security failure.

948
01:15:52.983 --> 01:15:57.558
The question is. will DGP Bitta take responsibility for his security failure?

949
01:15:57.830 --> 01:16:00.258
Human rights activist. Jaswant Singh

950
01:16:00.520 --> 01:16:04.287
is holding the Punjab Police responsible for the innocent lives lost

951
01:16:04.407 --> 01:16:10.328
and is demanding answers from the new CM. Gurcharan Singh Bohra. and DGP Bitta.

952
01:16:18.559 --> 01:16:22.051
'Verse chanting'

953
01:16:23.127 --> 01:16:24.471
And what does this mean?

954
01:16:24.740 --> 01:16:28.508
'Sorrow and suffering cannot touch those who walk with God.'

955
01:16:28.775 --> 01:16:31.739
Very good! - Thank you.

956
01:16:32.006 --> 01:16:36.048
Here Sanjiv. your tea. Come on. let's go Kiran.

957
01:16:36.168 --> 01:16:38.314
Coming. coming.

958
01:16:38.738 --> 01:16:40.351
Hurry up. Kiran.

959
01:16:40.904 --> 01:16:41.963
Bye! - Hurry up.

960
01:16:42.232 --> 01:16:43.041
Bye. bye..

961
01:16:45.734 --> 01:16:46.810
Sanjiv. you finish your tea.

962
01:16:46.930 --> 01:16:48.811
I'll just wash the car. then we'll leave together.

963
01:16:48.931 --> 01:16:49.738
Sure.

964
01:16:58.648 --> 01:17:00.808
Jaswant Singh... Come. we need to talk. - Talk about what?

965
01:17:00.928 --> 01:17:04.154
Come on. Get in! - But what's the matter? Sanjiv!

966
01:17:04.301 --> 01:17:05.648
Sanjiv! - Get inside!

967
01:17:06.996 --> 01:17:08.070
Sanjiv!

968
01:17:09.958 --> 01:17:12.379
Sanjiv! - Move it. come on!

969
01:17:12.499 --> 01:17:13.300
Sanjiv. come out!

970
01:17:14.002 --> 01:17:15.066
Sanjiv!

971
01:17:15.338 --> 01:17:16.951
Get lost! - Let's go. let's go!

972
01:17:17.223 --> 01:17:18.564
Drive. drive! - Stop!

973
01:17:18.684 --> 01:17:20.301
Come on. drive! Hurry up! - Stop the car!

974
01:17:47.900 --> 01:17:51.131
Long live Jaswant Singh!

975
01:17:51.251 --> 01:17:54.759
Bring back Jaswant Singh!

976
01:17:54.879 --> 01:17:57.828
More than 48 hours had passed since Jaswant Singh’s abduction.

977
01:17:58.669 --> 01:18:01.093
Protests and vigils broke out all over Punjab.

978
01:18:01.213 --> 01:18:02.557
Long live the 'brothers of the unclaimed'.

979
01:18:02.677 --> 01:18:04.287
And they all had one demand...

980
01:18:05.124 --> 01:18:06.477
‘Return Jaswant Singh’.

981
01:18:08.358 --> 01:18:10.237
Despite two eye-witnesses.

982
01:18:11.053 --> 01:18:14.817
the silence of the government echoed not just in Punjab.

983
01:18:15.898 --> 01:18:17.503
but all over the world.

984
01:18:18.043 --> 01:18:24.505
I urge the courts in India to conduct a fair and immediate investigation of this crime.

985
01:18:25.047 --> 01:18:28.541
And to demand justice for Jaswant Singh and his family.

986
01:18:29.349 --> 01:18:32.845
Is the silence of cremation grounds akin to peace?

987
01:18:33.923 --> 01:18:36.342
Are human rights only for the living?

988
01:18:36.890 --> 01:18:37.960
Not the dead?

989
01:18:39.039 --> 01:18:44.151
For raising these two questions. Jaswant Singh was abducted from his home in broad daylight.

990
01:18:44.689 --> 01:18:46.840
Only a few days ago. right here...

991
01:18:47.113 --> 01:18:51.953
Jaswant Singh told the world who’d be to blame if something were to happen to him.

992
01:18:52.766 --> 01:18:57.602
And I demand to know from this country’s Supreme Court and the Punjab government.

993
01:18:59.225 --> 01:19:00.839
Where is Jaswant Singh?

994
01:19:01.913 --> 01:19:04.334
People do not simply vanish into thin air.

995
01:19:05.145 --> 01:19:09.178
This court gives the Punjab Police two months...

996
01:19:09.990 --> 01:19:11.871
to find Jaswant Singh

997
01:19:12.409 --> 01:19:14.027
and present him in court.

998
01:19:14.295 --> 01:19:17.255
And if they are unsuccessful.

999
01:19:18.059 --> 01:19:21.019
the court will order a CBI inquiry into this case.

1000
01:19:22.098 --> 01:19:24.786
It’s a simple case of disappearance. Mr. Bohra.

1001
01:19:26.136 --> 01:19:27.744
There’s no conspiracy here.

1002
01:19:29.093 --> 01:19:31.516
This case has become an embarrassment for us.

1003
01:19:33.132 --> 01:19:34.746
Punjab's image is getting tainted.

1004
01:19:35.827 --> 01:19:38.510
And New Delhi isn’t happy about this either.

1005
01:19:40.129 --> 01:19:43.085
‘Image handling’ is a politician’s job. Mr. Bohra.

1006
01:19:44.163 --> 01:19:44.973
not the police’s.

1007
01:19:45.783 --> 01:19:48.469
I have eliminated militancy in Punjab.

1008
01:19:49.283 --> 01:19:53.314
And it was New Delhi that gave me this responsibility.

1009
01:19:54.403 --> 01:19:58.429
And when you’re dealing with terrorism. you have to be ruthless.

1010
01:19:59.775 --> 01:20:01.383
If I have blood on my hands.

1011
01:20:02.467 --> 01:20:03.544
so do they.

1012
01:20:05.159 --> 01:20:06.770
Times have changed. Mr. Bitta.

1013
01:20:08.387 --> 01:20:09.460
And so has New Delhi's intentions.

1014
01:20:11.093 --> 01:20:12.419
And as for Punjab...

1015
01:20:13.771 --> 01:20:16.462
I will not let it remain a police state any longer.

1016
01:20:17.540 --> 01:20:19.687
You did your job. Just step aside...

1017
01:20:20.511 --> 01:20:22.381
and let bureaucracy take over.

1018
01:20:22.922 --> 01:20:27.495
The Supreme Court has given you two months.

1019
01:20:28.838 --> 01:20:29.655
I suggest...

1020
01:20:30.721 --> 01:20:32.336
... you use it to find Jaswant Singh.

1021
01:20:33.152 --> 01:20:35.299
Jaswant Singh is a case of disappearance.

1022
01:20:37.186 --> 01:20:39.071
so it could take some time.

1023
01:20:39.608 --> 01:20:42.834
You’re retiring in three months. remember?

1024
01:20:44.189 --> 01:20:48.219
Your government has promised me an extension. Mr. Bohra.

1025
01:20:49.022 --> 01:20:52.258
Then let’s assume...

1026
01:20:52.378 --> 01:20:54.795
... you need Jaswant Singh’s signature on your extension letter.

1027
01:20:56.832 --> 01:20:57.905
Okay?

1028
01:21:00.062 --> 01:21:00.596
Sir.

1029
01:21:00.875 --> 01:21:04.095
In this country. things get done only when New Delhi gets moving.

1030
01:21:05.445 --> 01:21:08.135
The time given to the Punjab Police was up.

1031
01:21:08.944 --> 01:21:11.629
while international pressure kept mounting.

1032
01:21:13.246 --> 01:21:17.282
And the Supreme Court decided to hand this case to the CBI.

1033
01:21:17.563 --> 01:21:19.710
And finding Jaswant Singh...

1034
01:21:19.830 --> 01:21:21.178
was now my responsibility.

1035
01:21:47.166 --> 01:21:50.115
'Association of Disappeared People' 'Amritsar. Punjab'

1036
01:21:52.000 --> 01:21:52.802
Paramjit Kaur?

1037
01:21:54.945 --> 01:21:55.747
Yes?

1038
01:21:56.818 --> 01:21:57.617
That’s me.

1039
01:22:02.438 --> 01:22:05.912
Samudra Singh. Additional Director. CBI Delhi.

1040
01:22:07.522 --> 01:22:08.855
We need to talk to you.

1041
01:22:15.276 --> 01:22:16.077
6th September...

1042
01:22:18.226 --> 01:22:19.289
Forgive me...

1043
01:22:20.632 --> 01:22:23.303
You must have recalled this day several times.

1044
01:22:25.180 --> 01:22:26.245
But if you would still...

1045
01:22:27.050 --> 01:22:27.854
Sure.

1046
01:22:32.131 --> 01:22:35.075
Like every day. I left with the kids for school...

1047
01:22:35.611 --> 01:22:40.162
There was a police jeep parked at the turning with some men in plain clothes.

1048
01:22:40.697 --> 01:22:41.762
They were looking at me.

1049
01:22:42.040 --> 01:22:43.637
Do you recognise any of them?

1050
01:22:49.535 --> 01:22:50.060
Then?

1051
01:22:51.134 --> 01:22:52.200
Then around 9:30.

1052
01:22:52.737 --> 01:22:54.876
Hari Singh said there was an urgent phone call from home.

1053
01:22:56.215 --> 01:22:56.754
Hello...

1054
01:22:58.090 --> 01:22:58.886
Sanjiv?

1055
01:22:59.424 --> 01:23:00.759
It was Sanjiv on the call.

1056
01:23:02.102 --> 01:23:03.973
He told me what happened.

1057
01:23:04.777 --> 01:23:06.382
Sanjiv. the eye-witness?

1058
01:23:06.502 --> 01:23:07.568
Yes.

1059
01:23:09.324 --> 01:23:10.124
And the police?

1060
01:23:11.472 --> 01:23:12.803
Yeah. yeah. Jaswant Singh.

1061
01:23:14.139 --> 01:23:15.214
Everyone knows him.

1062
01:23:16.550 --> 01:23:17.884
He’s in the newspapers everyday.

1063
01:23:18.425 --> 01:23:21.631
But that doesn't mean we'll buy any story you sell.

1064
01:23:22.165 --> 01:23:24.040
He saw it with his own eyes.

1065
01:23:24.314 --> 01:23:26.447
They picked him up outside his house in broad daylight.

1066
01:23:26.567 --> 01:23:27.909
He must be mistaken.

1067
01:23:28.860 --> 01:23:31.533
Why would Tarn Taran cops pick up a guy in Amritsar?

1068
01:23:32.335 --> 01:23:33.677
It’s out of their jurisdiction.

1069
01:23:34.744 --> 01:23:37.153
You can't write cock-and-bull in the report.

1070
01:23:39.559 --> 01:23:40.629
Go on.

1071
01:23:46.253 --> 01:23:48.920
Some time later. I returned home with the kids.

1072
01:23:50.800 --> 01:23:54.006
It felt like all the cops in Amritsar were at my house.

1073
01:23:55.077 --> 01:23:56.414
Whether to support or to intimidate...

1074
01:23:57.223 --> 01:23:58.019
... was unclear.

1075
01:23:58.139 --> 01:23:59.743
'DISAPPEARED - JASWANT SINGH'

1076
01:24:00.428 --> 01:24:02.838
The police have written ‘disappeared’ and shut the files.

1077
01:24:03.635 --> 01:24:05.509
But we have no other choice.

1078
01:24:07.659 --> 01:24:09.524
We have to fight this fight ourselves.

1079
01:24:13.267 --> 01:24:14.072
Thank you.

1080
01:24:15.146 --> 01:24:17.283
We’ll meet again if we need to.

1081
01:24:18.352 --> 01:24:18.884
Goodbye.

1082
01:24:22.103 --> 01:24:23.434
At least they used to return the bodies before.

1083
01:24:24.243 --> 01:24:27.182
But seeing the condition they were returned in would make anyone rise up

1084
01:24:27.984 --> 01:24:30.929
That's why cops started declaring them ‘unclaimed’ and burning them.

1085
01:24:32.000 --> 01:24:33.883
Jaswant’s files have every little detail.

1086
01:24:34.688 --> 01:24:37.921
From the cremation lists to the municipality records.

1087
01:24:38.718 --> 01:24:40.605
But now you won’t find anything there either.

1088
01:24:40.725 --> 01:24:44.213
The government has sealed all the cremation records.

1089
01:24:44.902 --> 01:24:46.245
And whatever’s left...

1090
01:24:47.322 --> 01:24:47.857
... is here.

1091
01:24:48.669 --> 01:24:50.006
Approximately 6.500.

1092
01:25:01.299 --> 01:25:03.179
We were preparing to go to a press conference.

1093
01:25:04.792 --> 01:25:05.866
You see that terrace...

1094
01:25:07.751 --> 01:25:08.827
There was one lady.

1095
01:25:10.438 --> 01:25:11.509
I think she also saw.

1096
01:25:12.589 --> 01:25:17.157
I saw some men pushing Jaswant Singh into a red Omni.

1097
01:25:17.695 --> 01:25:19.573
I even tried to stop them.

1098
01:25:19.846 --> 01:25:23.067
I immediately recognised they were cops. Immediately. over here.

1099
01:25:23.608 --> 01:25:26.836
I saw DSP Jagpal Singh. SI Tejinder Singh

1100
01:25:26.956 --> 01:25:28.565
and SI Ajay Kumar.

1101
01:25:28.714 --> 01:25:31.668
And as I was working with Punjab Daily at that point of time.

1102
01:25:32.479 --> 01:25:35.972
I know it was Tarn Taran police which had abducted Mr. Jaswant Singh.

1103
01:25:37.048 --> 01:25:37.848
Myself Sanjiv Singh...

1104
01:25:38.393 --> 01:25:40.807
Punjab Daily. ex.

1105
01:25:46.195 --> 01:25:47.262
Was anyone else there?

1106
01:25:48.876 --> 01:25:49.412
Pardon?

1107
01:25:52.634 --> 01:25:56.401
There were 2-3 men in the Gypsy behind.

1108
01:25:56.946 --> 01:25:57.476
I...

1109
01:25:58.279 --> 01:25:59.893
I tried but...

1110
01:26:00.435 --> 01:26:02.590
I couldn’t get a good look.

1111
01:26:04.734 --> 01:26:07.689
At around 9:30 in the morning. I was coming home with groceries.

1112
01:26:09.036 --> 01:26:12.794
when I heard the sound of a car. Honking loudly.

1113
01:26:13.336 --> 01:26:15.752
I turned and saw a red Omni coming up really fast.

1114
01:26:16.829 --> 01:26:18.708
As it slowed down to take the turn.

1115
01:26:19.788 --> 01:26:21.399
my gaze fell inside the car.

1116
01:26:21.667 --> 01:26:24.355
“Tarn Taran police has abducted me!”

1117
01:26:24.630 --> 01:26:25.695
Jaswant Singh was inside.

1118
01:26:26.511 --> 01:26:27.578
What else did you see?

1119
01:26:28.930 --> 01:26:30.001
The car’s licence plate.

1120
01:26:31.610 --> 01:26:32.955
DMT-1313.

1121
01:26:34.570 --> 01:26:36.178
If you have to testify in court.

1122
01:26:38.064 --> 01:26:39.137
you won’t hesitate?

1123
01:26:44.512 --> 01:26:47.738
There were 3-4 men in a red car.

1124
01:26:48.820 --> 01:26:50.433
First they approached Jaswant Singh.

1125
01:26:51.232 --> 01:26:52.038
A few words were exchanged...

1126
01:26:53.114 --> 01:26:54.996
then they forced him into the car and left.

1127
01:26:55.802 --> 01:26:56.608
Were they cops?

1128
01:26:56.885 --> 01:26:57.685
No...

1129
01:26:58.760 --> 01:26:59.297
Can't say...

1130
01:27:00.106 --> 01:27:01.453
They were all in plain clothes.

1131
01:27:02.256 --> 01:27:03.864
Do you remember anyone's face?

1132
01:27:05.478 --> 01:27:08.707
No. they all had their backs towards me.

1133
01:27:08.978 --> 01:27:10.316
That's all I saw.

1134
01:27:13.813 --> 01:27:15.424
Is Tejinder there? - Who are you?

1135
01:27:16.238 --> 01:27:18.381
You can't just barge in... - Lady. leave the way.

1136
01:27:18.920 --> 01:27:19.726
Who are you?

1137
01:27:20.000 --> 01:27:21.605
CBI. Delhi.

1138
01:27:23.767 --> 01:27:24.560
Hold up. sir...

1139
01:27:25.375 --> 01:27:26.444
Where are you off to this bright and early?

1140
01:27:26.984 --> 01:27:29.403
Going to pick up the DSP. - I see...

1141
01:27:29.523 --> 01:27:30.059
You are...?

1142
01:27:30.477 --> 01:27:31.551
DSP Jagpal Singh?

1143
01:27:31.820 --> 01:27:32.356
Yes...

1144
01:27:33.166 --> 01:27:35.044
Let's pick him up together. - What?

1145
01:27:35.318 --> 01:27:37.464
Let's go! - Let go of my hand.

1146
01:27:43.112 --> 01:27:44.722
Looking sharp. inspector!

1147
01:27:46.067 --> 01:27:47.409
Need to talk to you. Let's go.

1148
01:27:49.294 --> 01:27:50.097
Come on.

1149
01:27:51.180 --> 01:27:52.246
What's the rush?

1150
01:27:53.060 --> 01:27:54.397
We're leaving for a colleague's wedding.

1151
01:27:55.748 --> 01:27:57.084
Come back in two days.

1152
01:28:01.653 --> 01:28:03.805
It's not your wedding. it's your colleague's.

1153
01:28:04.355 --> 01:28:05.686
It'll happen without you.

1154
01:28:05.965 --> 01:28:08.641
Picking us up like this without any prior notice...

1155
01:28:09.453 --> 01:28:10.253
It's not right.

1156
01:28:11.066 --> 01:28:13.749
Well. at least you can tell between right and wrong.

1157
01:28:14.558 --> 01:28:15.900
Now spill it. where is Jaswant Singh?

1158
01:28:16.709 --> 01:28:17.513
Jaswant Singh who?

1159
01:28:18.055 --> 01:28:19.931
Which Jaswant Singh are you talking about?

1160
01:28:21.009 --> 01:28:23.696
The one everyone in Punjab is talking about.

1161
01:28:25.047 --> 01:28:27.727
Delhi. London. Canada...

1162
01:28:28.538 --> 01:28:29.607
Everywhere.

1163
01:28:30.687 --> 01:28:31.764
He’s disappeared.

1164
01:28:33.650 --> 01:28:34.981
But we’ve written up a report.

1165
01:28:36.065 --> 01:28:37.674
The police is doing its job.

1166
01:28:38.214 --> 01:28:41.434
If the police was doing its job. we wouldn’t have had to come from Delhi.

1167
01:28:43.060 --> 01:28:44.663
I was at Hemkund Sahib Gurudwara to pay my respects.

1168
01:28:45.737 --> 01:28:48.430
And I wasn’t alone. There were 27 of us.

1169
01:28:51.651 --> 01:28:52.994
You can ask anyone.

1170
01:28:53.535 --> 01:28:54.611
You must have stayed the night then?

1171
01:28:56.759 --> 01:28:59.449
Devlok Guesthouse. It’s nearby. You can find out.

1172
01:28:59.718 --> 01:29:01.861
There are witnesses who saw you.

1173
01:29:02.136 --> 01:29:05.356
In Amritsar. on 6th September.

1174
01:29:06.166 --> 01:29:07.506
We have their testimony.

1175
01:29:08.315 --> 01:29:10.201
Their testimony is mistaken.

1176
01:29:11.538 --> 01:29:13.153
And who are these eye-witnesses?

1177
01:29:17.191 --> 01:29:19.064
You know what ‘alibi’ means?

1178
01:29:20.951 --> 01:29:22.558
Of course you do. you're CBI after all.

1179
01:29:24.443 --> 01:29:26.322
We’ve got 16 of them.

1180
01:29:28.206 --> 01:29:29.814
Ask anyone at the police station.

1181
01:29:31.969 --> 01:29:33.312
They’ll tell you where we were.

1182
01:29:37.883 --> 01:29:40.566
Looks like they’re all from the same school.

1183
01:29:49.710 --> 01:29:51.589
Let’s see.

1184
01:29:53.203 --> 01:29:56.428
Neither did we have any complaint about Jaswant Singh.

1185
01:29:56.711 --> 01:29:59.920
nor did anyone have anything against the man.

1186
01:30:01.536 --> 01:30:02.881
So why would we pick him up?

1187
01:30:04.493 --> 01:30:05.569
Without reason.

1188
01:30:06.375 --> 01:30:07.452
Reason?

1189
01:30:09.869 --> 01:30:10.941
Here’s the reason.

1190
01:30:21.158 --> 01:30:24.117
He exposed your entire operation.

1191
01:30:25.193 --> 01:30:26.530
In front of the whole world.

1192
01:30:26.802 --> 01:30:30.561
And for fear of enquiry. you made him disappear.

1193
01:30:32.719 --> 01:30:34.057
Who gave you the order?

1194
01:30:35.411 --> 01:30:36.478
Order...

1195
01:30:39.437 --> 01:30:41.853
We’ve always had only one order.

1196
01:30:43.736 --> 01:30:45.079
To eliminate terrorism.

1197
01:30:47.500 --> 01:30:48.309
At any cost.

1198
01:30:50.996 --> 01:30:52.334
You watch the news. don't you?

1199
01:30:55.026 --> 01:30:57.176
You see their weapons on the 9 o’ clock news.

1200
01:30:58.251 --> 01:31:03.623
AK-47. LMG. hand grenades. rocket launchers...

1201
01:31:06.044 --> 01:31:07.654
That’s what we’re fighting against.

1202
01:31:09.807 --> 01:31:11.150
For the last ten years.

1203
01:31:14.113 --> 01:31:15.179
Everyday.

1204
01:31:16.001 --> 01:31:17.062
Day and night.

1205
01:31:22.171 --> 01:31:23.517
You talk about orders.

1206
01:31:25.396 --> 01:31:27.815
Which of these weapons did Jaswant Singh have?

1207
01:31:37.225 --> 01:31:38.299
Who’s behind all this?

1208
01:31:42.870 --> 01:31:43.679
Sugga?

1209
01:31:46.095 --> 01:31:47.172
He’s in Chandigarh.

1210
01:31:49.059 --> 01:31:50.125
He's back in two days.

1211
01:31:54.705 --> 01:31:55.768
Ask him yourself.

1212
01:32:14.860 --> 01:32:15.662
Sir!

1213
01:32:20.235 --> 01:32:22.114
1313 red Omni. It's one of your cars?

1214
01:32:22.389 --> 01:32:23.994
Of course it’s mine. sir.

1215
01:32:24.268 --> 01:32:28.022
Number one taxi service from Jalandhar to Ludhiana.

1216
01:32:29.644 --> 01:32:31.524
Where was your 1313 on 6th September?

1217
01:32:33.136 --> 01:32:34.740
Probably on a booking. sir.

1218
01:32:36.354 --> 01:32:37.437
Why. what happened?

1219
01:32:39.849 --> 01:32:41.460
There’s no entry in your bill book.

1220
01:32:42.811 --> 01:32:44.687
It’s just crossed out in red here.

1221
01:32:45.227 --> 01:32:48.192
Oh. that’s our code for government bookings.

1222
01:32:49.263 --> 01:32:53.564
No entries or bookings needed for you folks obviously.

1223
01:32:54.368 --> 01:32:54.901
Right?

1224
01:32:56.250 --> 01:32:58.127
Us folks? What do you mean?

1225
01:32:58.404 --> 01:33:00.547
It’s clear. isn’t it?

1226
01:33:00.820 --> 01:33:02.702
You folks... cops.

1227
01:33:03.507 --> 01:33:04.307
And who were these cops?

1228
01:33:04.582 --> 01:33:08.612
Inspector Shivender Singh and SI Harinder Singh.

1229
01:33:09.688 --> 01:33:11.028
From Tarn Taran.

1230
01:33:12.375 --> 01:33:13.721
They took the car.

1231
01:33:14.258 --> 01:33:15.062
When did they take it?

1232
01:33:15.334 --> 01:33:18.288
On 5th evening. They said they were going out of town.

1233
01:33:19.092 --> 01:33:22.319
But they brought the car back in two days. on the 7th.

1234
01:33:24.469 --> 01:33:25.814
But sir. what’s the matter?

1235
01:33:27.160 --> 01:33:28.769
Where’s your 1313 right now?

1236
01:33:48.122 --> 01:33:49.195
Hold my beer.

1237
01:34:23.070 --> 01:34:23.875
Your acquaintance?

1238
01:34:25.761 --> 01:34:26.827
Greetings.

1239
01:34:27.645 --> 01:34:28.975
We’re friends of the groom.

1240
01:34:29.257 --> 01:34:29.787
I see.

1241
01:34:29.907 --> 01:34:31.523
Just arrived from Delhi.

1242
01:34:31.643 --> 01:34:32.982
From Delhi? - Yes.

1243
01:34:33.102 --> 01:34:34.984
To surprise him. - Oh wow...

1244
01:34:35.165 --> 01:34:35.966
And you?

1245
01:34:36.782 --> 01:34:37.310
Myself?

1246
01:34:38.925 --> 01:34:39.729
Harinder Singh.

1247
01:34:40.000 --> 01:34:40.804
Sub-insector.

1248
01:34:41.339 --> 01:34:42.414
Tarn Taran police.

1249
01:34:43.212 --> 01:34:45.623
Best man and best friend.

1250
01:34:45.743 --> 01:34:47.078
Oh wonderful!

1251
01:34:47.497 --> 01:34:49.099
And where is Mr. Inspector?

1252
01:34:49.219 --> 01:34:50.286
Mr. Inspector?

1253
01:34:50.439 --> 01:34:53.115
Come with me. I’ll take you to him.

1254
01:34:53.390 --> 01:34:54.992
Come on.

1255
01:34:55.267 --> 01:34:56.864
Let's make you meet your friend.

1256
01:34:58.740 --> 01:35:00.876
Mind the step. Mind it.

1257
01:35:03.822 --> 01:35:04.619
Mr. Inspector.

1258
01:35:05.964 --> 01:35:08.371
Mr. Inspector!

1259
01:35:10.243 --> 01:35:12.653
Look who it is!

1260
01:35:17.205 --> 01:35:18.540
Surprise!

1261
01:35:20.956 --> 01:35:21.483
Who are they?

1262
01:35:23.633 --> 01:35:24.963
Not friends?

1263
01:35:29.249 --> 01:35:30.319
CBI. Delhi.

1264
01:35:34.870 --> 01:35:36.203
Congratulations on the wedding.

1265
01:35:44.236 --> 01:35:45.302
I was there only...

1266
01:35:46.378 --> 01:35:47.444
... on 6th September.

1267
01:35:48.527 --> 01:35:49.586
In Dharamshala.

1268
01:35:52.003 --> 01:35:52.801
For my engagement.

1269
01:35:55.754 --> 01:35:56.813
You took this Omni?

1270
01:35:58.153 --> 01:35:59.224
1313?

1271
01:36:07.256 --> 01:36:08.324
You were with him as well?

1272
01:36:11.271 --> 01:36:12.345
You were with him?

1273
01:36:12.873 --> 01:36:14.221
Yeah. so?

1274
01:36:19.029 --> 01:36:21.703
This Omni was used to adbuct Jaswant Singh on 6th September.

1275
01:36:24.117 --> 01:36:25.454
There are eye-witnesses.

1276
01:36:26.794 --> 01:36:28.129
They’re mistaken.

1277
01:36:28.934 --> 01:36:30.542
I was on leave from the 5th.

1278
01:36:30.811 --> 01:36:31.605
Really?

1279
01:36:32.419 --> 01:36:35.899
We found an entry in your name at Kang police station. on 5th September.

1280
01:36:36.695 --> 01:36:38.566
You locked up some Kehar Singh there.

1281
01:36:39.371 --> 01:36:41.519
How? You were on leave.

1282
01:36:44.725 --> 01:36:46.064
And why did you put him in Kang?

1283
01:36:48.203 --> 01:36:49.272
Isn’t he in charge there?

1284
01:36:51.949 --> 01:36:53.824
First I took him to Tarn Taran and Jhabal.

1285
01:36:54.630 --> 01:36:56.768
Cells were full so I brought him to Kang.

1286
01:36:58.912 --> 01:37:00.244
And? - And nothing.

1287
01:37:01.588 --> 01:37:03.464
I left for Dharamshala the next day.

1288
01:37:05.070 --> 01:37:06.136
On 6th September.

1289
01:37:06.672 --> 01:37:07.474
You can check if you want.

1290
01:37:08.814 --> 01:37:10.149
Oh I’ve checked everything.

1291
01:37:12.569 --> 01:37:16.034
It takes half a lifetime for a sub-inspector to make inspector.

1292
01:37:17.917 --> 01:37:19.789
You made it in less than ten months.

1293
01:37:21.395 --> 01:37:22.465
And in these ten months.

1294
01:37:22.585 --> 01:37:24.457
both your names are mentioned

1295
01:37:25.682 --> 01:37:28.083
in firewood receipts of 21 unclaimed cremations.

1296
01:37:29.691 --> 01:37:30.224
How come?

1297
01:37:32.640 --> 01:37:37.184
I guess only your Jaswant Singh can answer that question.

1298
01:37:38.259 --> 01:37:40.130
And where is our Jaswant Singh?

1299
01:37:43.607 --> 01:37:45.214
Since you’ve found out this much already...

1300
01:37:46.285 --> 01:37:47.084
Find him as well.

1301
01:37:50.030 --> 01:37:51.633
You’ll get all your answers.

1302
01:37:55.386 --> 01:37:57.791
Jaswant Singh was a known name.

1303
01:37:58.867 --> 01:38:02.347
So they would never make the mistake of keeping him in Tarn Taran or Jhabal.

1304
01:38:05.556 --> 01:38:06.623
On 5th September.

1305
01:38:07.428 --> 01:38:09.576
Kehar Singh was detained in Kang police station.

1306
01:38:09.696 --> 01:38:10.759
Why?

1307
01:38:10.908 --> 01:38:12.510
Because they had empty cells.

1308
01:38:13.049 --> 01:38:15.724
And on 7th September. he was released.

1309
01:38:17.868 --> 01:38:20.544
And Jaswant Singh was abducted on 6th September.

1310
01:38:22.694 --> 01:38:24.556
Maybe they brought him here too.

1311
01:38:26.967 --> 01:38:27.774
Kang police station.

1312
01:38:33.395 --> 01:38:35.798
And only one person can confirm this.

1313
01:38:37.943 --> 01:38:39.014
Kehar Singh.

1314
01:39:01.762 --> 01:39:04.438
I had a hearing in court on the 5th.

1315
01:39:06.043 --> 01:39:11.128
After that. they detained me for two days.

1316
01:39:12.207 --> 01:39:13.537
At Kang police station.

1317
01:39:14.342 --> 01:39:15.411
Was anyone else there?

1318
01:39:17.019 --> 01:39:19.962
No sir... not on the first night.

1319
01:39:20.763 --> 01:39:21.303
Then...

1320
01:39:21.835 --> 01:39:25.053
... on the second day. they brought someone in the next cell.

1321
01:39:26.385 --> 01:39:27.451
Who was it?

1322
01:39:29.330 --> 01:39:30.933
Anything you saw. or remember?

1323
01:39:31.472 --> 01:39:33.345
No I didn’t see him.

1324
01:39:34.151 --> 01:39:35.754
But I heard his name.

1325
01:39:36.826 --> 01:39:38.159
Some Jaswant Singh.

1326
01:39:50.208 --> 01:39:51.542
Think hard.

1327
01:39:53.152 --> 01:39:54.486
You sure you heard Jaswant Singh?

1328
01:39:55.828 --> 01:39:57.986
Yes. it was Jaswant Singh.

1329
01:39:59.330 --> 01:40:04.981
All the cops were shouting his name. abusing him.

1330
01:40:06.329 --> 01:40:07.950
Then later...

1331
01:40:08.218 --> 01:40:10.101
... the SSP himself showed up.

1332
01:40:11.448 --> 01:40:14.412
And he started beating him.

1333
01:40:18.728 --> 01:40:19.525
Then?

1334
01:40:20.339 --> 01:40:23.028
Then they left after a while.

1335
01:40:23.847 --> 01:40:27.614
leaving one cop behind to stand guard.

1336
01:40:29.761 --> 01:40:30.572
What’s his name?

1337
01:40:32.729 --> 01:40:36.776
Don’t know his name. sir. He wasn't in uniform.

1338
01:40:37.573 --> 01:40:40.272
But yes... he had green eyes.

1339
01:40:41.352 --> 01:40:42.430
Like emeralds.

1340
01:40:43.230 --> 01:40:45.934
He brought me food that night.

1341
01:40:51.847 --> 01:40:52.923
Will you be an official witness?

1342
01:40:53.738 --> 01:40:54.272
What?

1343
01:40:56.160 --> 01:40:57.503
Will you testify?

1344
01:41:03.161 --> 01:41:05.854
We sold the farm to bring him back once already.

1345
01:41:06.666 --> 01:41:09.354
If they pick him up again. I have nothing left to sell.

1346
01:41:12.058 --> 01:41:13.127
Don’t worry.

1347
01:41:15.824 --> 01:41:17.166
I’ll guarantee his safety.

1348
01:41:22.016 --> 01:41:24.978
Pack of mongrels hunting for scraps.

1349
01:41:27.141 --> 01:41:29.290
Let’s see how long they bark.

1350
01:41:30.373 --> 01:41:32.518
As long as they bark and don't bite. sir.

1351
01:41:33.057 --> 01:41:34.941
Sniffing around as they please.

1352
01:41:36.030 --> 01:41:37.096
Wherever.

1353
01:41:37.643 --> 01:41:39.254
They picked me up before my vows.

1354
01:41:40.062 --> 01:41:42.213
Humiliated me in front of 400 guests.

1355
01:41:43.030 --> 01:41:44.371
Then made me sit around all night.

1356
01:41:45.718 --> 01:41:47.332
Is it right. sir?

1357
01:41:47.872 --> 01:41:50.027
They raided three police stations last evening.

1358
01:41:53.531 --> 01:41:54.876
Picked up some files as well.

1359
01:41:56.765 --> 01:41:58.918
When there’s nothing in those files.

1360
01:42:00.806 --> 01:42:01.612
what will they find?

1361
01:42:04.306 --> 01:42:05.107
Get the bottle!

1362
01:42:07.807 --> 01:42:10.227
When you’ve done nothing wrong.

1363
01:42:11.842 --> 01:42:12.929
why are you worried?

1364
01:42:14.270 --> 01:42:15.613
Just remember...

1365
01:42:16.961 --> 01:42:18.578
that we are Punjab Police.

1366
01:42:21.001 --> 01:42:22.888
And as far as I remember.

1367
01:42:23.698 --> 01:42:27.469
the name of this state is still Punjab.

1368
01:42:29.085 --> 01:42:30.159
Hasn’t changed.

1369
01:42:32.585 --> 01:42:33.661
Got it?

1370
01:42:39.588 --> 01:42:40.397
Okay...

1371
01:42:41.471 --> 01:42:42.548
Now. get lost.

1372
01:42:44.168 --> 01:42:44.974
Sir.

1373
01:43:16.218 --> 01:43:17.022
6th September.

1374
01:43:18.911 --> 01:43:20.255
Remember where you were?

1375
01:43:22.140 --> 01:43:22.957
Chandigarh.

1376
01:43:25.108 --> 01:43:26.181
At my niece’s wedding.

1377
01:43:28.073 --> 01:43:29.683
I kept a prayer on the 6th.

1378
01:43:32.119 --> 01:43:33.723
You must be knowing Jaswant Singh.

1379
01:43:35.343 --> 01:43:36.414
The human rights fellow...

1380
01:43:37.773 --> 01:43:39.110
... who’s disappeared these days.

1381
01:43:40.459 --> 01:43:41.540
I’ve seen him in newspapers.

1382
01:43:50.155 --> 01:43:54.728
Jaswant Singh mentioned you in his last speech.

1383
01:43:55.274 --> 01:43:57.967
And he also said that if anything happens to him.

1384
01:44:00.390 --> 01:44:02.273
... then who would be responsible.

1385
01:44:05.517 --> 01:44:06.315
Anything to say?

1386
01:44:13.051 --> 01:44:14.395
You’re an educated man.

1387
01:44:17.629 --> 01:44:18.972
Tell me something.

1388
01:44:21.673 --> 01:44:23.011
Today if I say...

1389
01:44:24.363 --> 01:44:26.514
if something happens to me then you’ll be responsible.

1390
01:44:28.403 --> 01:44:30.556
and if something actually happens to me tomorrow...

1391
01:44:31.904 --> 01:44:32.982
then are you responsible?

1392
01:44:35.143 --> 01:44:36.210
You’ll go to jail?

1393
01:44:48.871 --> 01:44:49.683
Tea.

1394
01:44:52.103 --> 01:44:55.873
You’re involved in over a thousand abductions and extrajudicial killings.

1395
01:44:56.956 --> 01:44:59.912
So it's clear why he’d take your name.

1396
01:45:02.338 --> 01:45:04.498
Extrajudicial killings.

1397
01:45:06.652 --> 01:45:09.070
You were in Delhi Police before you joined the CBI. right?

1398
01:45:10.419 --> 01:45:11.228
In ’86?

1399
01:45:15.000 --> 01:45:18.502
You were present in Delhi’s Trilokpuri riots in ’84. weren’t you?

1400
01:45:23.354 --> 01:45:24.980
How many did you kill in ’84?

1401
01:45:26.603 --> 01:45:28.207
And which killings were those?

1402
01:45:29.289 --> 01:45:31.175
Judicial or extrajudicial?

1403
01:45:37.926 --> 01:45:38.457
Sugar?

1404
01:45:44.122 --> 01:45:46.275
You don’t have the depth. Samudra Singh.

1405
01:45:48.432 --> 01:45:50.868
to conceal all the secrets of ’84.

1406
01:45:57.334 --> 01:45:58.677
Mr. Sugga.

1407
01:46:01.379 --> 01:46:04.341
Recounting ’84 won’t change the figures of ’95.

1408
01:46:06.230 --> 01:46:08.386
It’s not just about one Jaswant Singh.

1409
01:46:10.007 --> 01:46:11.622
It’s about thousands more.

1410
01:46:14.055 --> 01:46:15.396
You’ll have to account for them.

1411
01:46:17.825 --> 01:46:19.980
Punjab’s account has always been complicated.

1412
01:46:25.381 --> 01:46:29.959
We’re fighting those who don’t get captured. only killed.

1413
01:46:32.396 --> 01:46:35.623
They killed DIG Sabarwal on the steps of the Golden Temple.

1414
01:46:38.052 --> 01:46:41.015
Nobody went near the body for six hours.

1415
01:46:43.173 --> 01:46:46.147
You need to call the army to kill these people.

1416
01:46:48.838 --> 01:46:51.531
Even cannons fall short.

1417
01:46:52.881 --> 01:46:56.384
One bullet of ours is fired in response to how many of theirs...

1418
01:46:58.007 --> 01:46:59.891
an outsider like you won’t understand.

1419
01:47:06.364 --> 01:47:07.715
You know what a vice is?

1420
01:47:11.753 --> 01:47:13.918
You have your head in a vice.

1421
01:47:15.803 --> 01:47:17.694
Pressure from above or below...

1422
01:47:19.310 --> 01:47:20.656
You’re the one getting squeezed.

1423
01:47:22.813 --> 01:47:25.778
Sooner or later. you’ll have to answer for Jaswant Singh.

1424
01:47:26.317 --> 01:47:29.012
Here... or in court.

1425
01:47:31.171 --> 01:47:31.981
Remember that.

1426
01:47:33.325 --> 01:47:34.677
We’ll meet again.

1427
01:47:41.151 --> 01:47:44.658
It’s been two-and-a-half months since Jaswant Singh’s disappearance.

1428
01:47:46.000 --> 01:47:49.502
But the Punjab government is still silent.

1429
01:47:50.860 --> 01:47:52.464
Perhaps they aren’t aware

1430
01:47:53.276 --> 01:47:57.312
that Jaswant Singh isn’t just the name of a man.

1431
01:47:57.854 --> 01:48:00.813
Jaswant Singh is the name of a cause.

1432
01:48:01.626 --> 01:48:03.239
This is no ordinary fight.

1433
01:48:04.061 --> 01:48:06.741
but the fight of a brother of the unclaimed.

1434
01:48:07.284 --> 01:48:10.780
who openly challenged the government.

1435
01:48:11.590 --> 01:48:13.742
This is a fight for what's right.

1436
01:48:14.017 --> 01:48:17.245
Jaswant Singh! Jaswant Singh!

1437
01:48:17.517 --> 01:48:19.946
Brothers of the Unclaimed!

1438
01:48:20.066 --> 01:48:29.486
Jaswant Singh! Jaswant Singh!

1439
01:48:29.915 --> 01:48:32.057
I quit the job at the library.

1440
01:48:36.374 --> 01:48:38.255
This fight is a full-time job.

1441
01:48:40.142 --> 01:48:41.216
What brings you here?

1442
01:48:47.146 --> 01:48:48.491
We found a new witness.

1443
01:48:48.762 --> 01:48:49.571
Kehar Singh.

1444
01:48:50.916 --> 01:48:52.798
He says that on 6th September...

1445
01:48:53.610 --> 01:48:55.773
Jaswant Singh was held at Kang police station.

1446
01:48:56.303 --> 01:48:57.919
In the next cell.

1447
01:48:59.001 --> 01:49:01.152
Now we have three witnesses.

1448
01:49:01.963 --> 01:49:03.306
And very soon.

1449
01:49:03.426 --> 01:49:05.581
we'll appeal to the court for the hearing.

1450
01:50:09.032 --> 01:50:09.572
Anyone home?

1451
01:50:28.427 --> 01:50:29.227
Sugga.

1452
01:50:33.548 --> 01:50:35.157
Diwali is in two days.

1453
01:50:36.235 --> 01:50:37.580
so I brought something for the kids.

1454
01:50:45.393 --> 01:50:46.472
Sparklers.

1455
01:50:48.364 --> 01:50:49.698
Bomb?

1456
01:50:50.509 --> 01:50:52.393
How about a spinner?

1457
01:50:53.745 --> 01:50:54.276
Spinner.

1458
01:51:01.825 --> 01:51:03.435
Here. go play. Spinner.

1459
01:51:17.993 --> 01:51:19.057
Stubborn.

1460
01:51:21.754 --> 01:51:22.828
Like his father.

1461
01:51:27.151 --> 01:51:28.759
I won’t lie. sister.

1462
01:51:30.921 --> 01:51:31.986
Small. big.

1463
01:51:33.337 --> 01:51:34.417
old. young...

1464
01:51:36.570 --> 01:51:37.643
I’ve killed many.

1465
01:51:39.805 --> 01:51:41.967
But I didn’t touch your Jaswant Singh.

1466
01:51:45.724 --> 01:51:47.881
We want to help you.

1467
01:51:49.500 --> 01:51:50.844
We want to find him and bring him to you.

1468
01:51:52.733 --> 01:51:54.077
Then find him.

1469
01:51:55.421 --> 01:51:57.306
It’s your duty.

1470
01:51:59.464 --> 01:52:00.538
But how?

1471
01:52:02.968 --> 01:52:05.117
You’re blaming us as well. aren’t you?

1472
01:52:11.048 --> 01:52:13.738
Retract your statement against the police.

1473
01:52:19.124 --> 01:52:20.203
And we’ll find him and bring him back.

1474
01:52:21.823 --> 01:52:22.898
To you.

1475
01:52:23.977 --> 01:52:24.782
To your kids.

1476
01:52:28.023 --> 01:52:30.979
Then you can take asylum. America. Canada. London...

1477
01:52:31.521 --> 01:52:32.321
wherever.

1478
01:52:37.441 --> 01:52:38.789
And we’ll forget everything as well.

1479
01:52:46.611 --> 01:52:50.646
Even Jaswant Singh wouldn’t agree to return on these terms.

1480
01:52:51.184 --> 01:52:52.791
So how will you bring him?

1481
01:52:54.146 --> 01:52:56.568
You don’t know Jaswant Singh.

1482
01:52:58.990 --> 01:52:59.799
I do.

1483
01:53:05.724 --> 01:53:06.803
You can leave.

1484
01:53:15.154 --> 01:53:16.767
And please take these with you.

1485
01:53:20.000 --> 01:53:21.334
Put them up in your police station.

1486
01:53:22.135 --> 01:53:23.470
It'll be appreciated.

1487
01:53:35.726 --> 01:53:37.862
Since you know Jaswant Singh so well...

1488
01:53:42.391 --> 01:53:44.251
Then know this as well.

1489
01:53:46.652 --> 01:53:50.383
If I have to answer for 25.000 corpses.

1490
01:53:52.524 --> 01:53:54.648
Then I’ll answer for 25.001.

1491
01:53:59.714 --> 01:54:00.776
Remember that.

1492
01:54:29.834 --> 01:54:30.363
Sir...

1493
01:54:31.697 --> 01:54:32.766
End of an era.

1494
01:54:35.961 --> 01:54:37.826
My untimely retirement

1495
01:54:38.370 --> 01:54:40.491
is a new year's gift to the militants.

1496
01:54:41.023 --> 01:54:43.429
I hope the new government has thought this through.

1497
01:54:44.226 --> 01:54:46.888
And I also hope that Mr. Varma

1498
01:54:47.429 --> 01:54:51.418
continues to preserve the dignity of the uniform. as I have.

1499
01:54:52.757 --> 01:54:54.621
I’m not much of a speech man.

1500
01:54:55.686 --> 01:54:58.354
I prefer to be brief and straight.

1501
01:55:00.480 --> 01:55:04.214
My aim is to sanitize and sensitize the force.

1502
01:55:05.011 --> 01:55:06.875
without lowering our guard.

1503
01:55:07.689 --> 01:55:08.743
For the past few years.

1504
01:55:10.612 --> 01:55:13.541
because of a few police officers.

1505
01:55:14.343 --> 01:55:15.938
not just Punjab Police.

1506
01:55:16.475 --> 01:55:19.139
but the whole state has suffered disrepute.

1507
01:55:20.215 --> 01:55:21.002
But...

1508
01:55:21.806 --> 01:55:23.938
we will not repeat their mistakes.

1509
01:55:25.000 --> 01:55:27.710
And for this I need your support.

1510
01:55:28.785 --> 01:55:33.382
The fear that Punjab’s people have of the police...

1511
01:55:34.725 --> 01:55:38.506
First we must eliminate that fear.

1512
01:55:39.314 --> 01:55:42.013
And we must win back their trust.

1513
01:55:42.563 --> 01:55:45.795
I’m sure I have your full support in this mission.

1514
01:55:49.037 --> 01:55:50.115
Thank you.

1515
01:56:00.378 --> 01:56:03.348
‘Devil in Police Uniform.’

1516
01:56:06.593 --> 01:56:08.209
‘Butcher of Gurdaspur.’

1517
01:56:23.341 --> 01:56:24.411
‘Police or...

1518
01:56:26.299 --> 01:56:27.380
ex... executioner’.

1519
01:56:29.544 --> 01:56:32.517
What are the newspapers writing about you...

1520
01:56:33.057 --> 01:56:34.133
Ever read them?

1521
01:56:40.610 --> 01:56:43.315
Now... where is Jaswant Singh?

1522
01:56:44.934 --> 01:56:45.478
Sir?

1523
01:56:49.259 --> 01:56:50.067
Jaswant Singh.

1524
01:56:53.307 --> 01:56:54.114
He’s disappeared. sir.

1525
01:56:56.818 --> 01:56:58.704
But we’re trying our best to find him.

1526
01:56:59.788 --> 01:57:04.377
You’ve been trying for over two months.

1527
01:57:05.456 --> 01:57:07.885
It takes some time. sir.

1528
01:57:15.188 --> 01:57:16.257
Surjit Singh.

1529
01:57:18.151 --> 01:57:20.847
I was DGP Intelligence before this.

1530
01:57:22.203 --> 01:57:23.814
I know you very well.

1531
01:57:25.983 --> 01:57:27.595
The CBI is already on your tail.

1532
01:57:28.679 --> 01:57:30.570
An inquiry could start any day.

1533
01:57:31.653 --> 01:57:34.619
Then all your pending cases will reopen.

1534
01:57:36.778 --> 01:57:38.669
Getting away this time

1535
01:57:39.484 --> 01:57:41.102
won't be so easy for you.

1536
01:57:43.534 --> 01:57:45.692
You have seven days.

1537
01:57:47.045 --> 01:57:48.662
I want Jaswant Singh.

1538
01:57:49.742 --> 01:57:50.822
At any cost.

1539
01:57:56.492 --> 01:57:57.572
Seven days.

1540
01:58:02.701 --> 01:58:03.247
Yes. sir.

1541
01:58:04.056 --> 01:58:05.671
He’s given me seven days.

1542
01:58:06.756 --> 01:58:08.103
He says find Jaswant Singh.

1543
01:58:08.923 --> 01:58:11.074
How do I find him. you tell me?

1544
01:58:24.038 --> 01:58:26.195
The CBI has a hearing date from the court.

1545
01:58:27.551 --> 01:58:28.896
There were two eye-witnesses.

1546
01:58:29.979 --> 01:58:31.063
Now there are three.

1547
01:58:33.218 --> 01:58:35.648
Forget Jaswant Singh for now and find out...

1548
01:58:37.000 --> 01:58:38.345
who this third joker is.

1549
01:59:10.541 --> 01:59:13.222
Move ahead. - Come. next.

1550
01:59:14.564 --> 01:59:16.171
Stop right there - CBI. Delhi.

1551
01:59:16.712 --> 01:59:18.318
Here they come sniffing around.

1552
01:59:18.862 --> 01:59:21.536
You finish your report. and meet me at the station.

1553
01:59:21.808 --> 01:59:22.345
Yes sir.

1554
01:59:22.616 --> 01:59:23.953
Killed in a raid last night.

1555
01:59:39.259 --> 01:59:40.864
There’s no one home.

1556
01:59:40.984 --> 01:59:43.660
Mr. Sanjiv left with his family two days ago.

1557
01:59:44.347 --> 01:59:45.690
Did he say where they’re going?

1558
01:59:45.810 --> 01:59:48.224
No. he didn’t say and I didn’t ask.

1559
01:59:49.176 --> 01:59:49.980
They’ve left.

1560
01:59:50.786 --> 01:59:52.396
Harpal’s house is also locked. sir.

1561
01:59:53.204 --> 01:59:54.011
It’s empty.

1562
01:59:57.501 --> 01:59:58.836
This is nothing...

1563
01:59:59.377 --> 02:00:02.589
... but a complete mockery of the judicial system.

1564
02:00:03.136 --> 02:00:05.014
There were three strong witnesses in this case.

1565
02:00:06.349 --> 02:00:07.418
Two of them are missing.

1566
02:00:07.692 --> 02:00:09.031
.... and one ends up dead.

1567
02:00:09.301 --> 02:00:10.643
Just one day before the hearing.

1568
02:00:11.183 --> 02:00:12.788
And the irony of the matter is...

1569
02:00:13.059 --> 02:00:17.894
that despite several loopholes in their alibis. these cops are still serving in the force.

1570
02:00:18.693 --> 02:00:23.518
But Mr. Jais. there has to be at least one strong piece of evidence to back up your claims.

1571
02:00:23.792 --> 02:00:25.134
Just this isn’t enough.

1572
02:00:29.426 --> 02:00:30.499
Your honour...

1573
02:00:31.842 --> 02:00:32.649
A family...

1574
02:00:33.718 --> 02:00:36.136
breaks their back day and night

1575
02:00:36.405 --> 02:00:39.351
to raise and educate their kids.

1576
02:00:39.896 --> 02:00:43.106
Then one day those kids. no more than 20-22 years old. disappear.

1577
02:00:43.654 --> 02:00:45.257
When they don’t return in a few days. the parents

1578
02:00:46.064 --> 02:00:49.017
go to the police. where they are turned away.

1579
02:00:49.280 --> 02:00:51.962
In fact they are told that their kids...

1580
02:00:52.775 --> 02:00:53.840
... are with terrorists.

1581
02:00:54.111 --> 02:00:55.719
For a little bit of money. you'll get them back.

1582
02:00:55.990 --> 02:00:57.059
Objection. your honour!

1583
02:00:58.142 --> 02:01:00.017
Irrelevant to the case. - Mr. Dahiya. please...

1584
02:01:00.284 --> 02:01:01.355
Overruled. - Let me finish.

1585
02:01:01.475 --> 02:01:03.353
Mr. Jais. come to the point quickly.

1586
02:01:04.572 --> 02:01:05.380
Your honour.

1587
02:01:06.191 --> 02:01:09.943
by the time the parents somehow gather the money.

1588
02:01:10.063 --> 02:01:13.818
some other cop shows up and buys those kids for a higher sum.

1589
02:01:14.237 --> 02:01:18.259
and then kills them along with the terrorists.

1590
02:01:18.534 --> 02:01:19.868
And we all know the reason.

1591
02:01:20.410 --> 02:01:23.896
Because more dead militants equals bigger promotions. Am I right?

1592
02:01:24.170 --> 02:01:26.575
Objection. your honour! - Overruled.

1593
02:01:29.259 --> 02:01:30.868
But it doesn’t end there.

1594
02:01:32.749 --> 02:01:34.895
Then it's the turn of the poor parents.

1595
02:01:35.431 --> 02:01:37.312
Those aged. helpless parents...

1596
02:01:37.432 --> 02:01:40.914
are then harassed by branding their children as terrorists.

1597
02:01:41.336 --> 02:01:42.675
And you know why?

1598
02:01:42.947 --> 02:01:45.087
To extort from them the same money

1599
02:01:45.362 --> 02:01:48.311
they had arranged to save their children.

1600
02:01:48.581 --> 02:01:49.654
Objection!

1601
02:01:49.934 --> 02:01:52.067
This is a blatant attempt to slander the police.

1602
02:01:52.339 --> 02:01:53.412
Then tell me this...

1603
02:01:53.947 --> 02:01:56.628
How are these cops. who were constables ten months ago.

1604
02:01:56.748 --> 02:02:00.236
sitting here as Inspectors today? Do you have an answer?

1605
02:02:00.659 --> 02:02:03.337
Your honour. the prosecution is insulting the court with these fake stories.

1606
02:02:03.607 --> 02:02:05.484
These are not stories. your honour.

1607
02:02:05.604 --> 02:02:08.020
These are the details of the petitions that those parents

1608
02:02:08.140 --> 02:02:11.096
had filed against these policemen in the high court.

1609
02:02:11.216 --> 02:02:12.549
Please have a look at this.

1610
02:02:14.877 --> 02:02:16.482
And these are the same officers. your honour...

1611
02:02:17.298 --> 02:02:19.703
... that the eye-witnesses saw abducting Jaswant Singh.

1612
02:02:20.240 --> 02:02:21.588
Their recorded testimonies are included.

1613
02:02:22.389 --> 02:02:23.459
But the trouble is...

1614
02:02:23.730 --> 02:02:28.017
that they either turn hostile out of fear. or turn up dead like Kehar Singh!

1615
02:02:28.297 --> 02:02:30.973
The prosecution is making wild accusations without any proof.

1616
02:02:31.093 --> 02:02:33.238
Mr. Dahiya. please... - Mr. Dahiya...

1617
02:02:34.999 --> 02:02:39.022
Due to the serious allegations and suspicious nature of this case.

1618
02:02:39.293 --> 02:02:41.172
in the interest of public security.

1619
02:02:41.449 --> 02:02:42.779
this court determines that

1620
02:02:42.899 --> 02:02:44.516
DSP Jagpal Singh.

1621
02:02:44.657 --> 02:02:46.539
Inspector Shivender Singh.

1622
02:02:46.810 --> 02:02:51.904
sub-inspector Tejinder Singh. sub-inspector Harinder Singh. inspector Ajay Kumar.

1623
02:02:52.176 --> 02:02:57.538
and SSP Surjit Singh Sugga should be suspended on immediate basis.

1624
02:02:58.341 --> 02:02:59.688
until the final hearing.

1625
02:03:05.055 --> 02:03:06.389
The court is adjourned.

1626
02:03:14.174 --> 02:03:14.976
Told you...

1627
02:03:18.205 --> 02:03:19.268
you’re the one getting squeezed.

1628
02:03:22.493 --> 02:03:24.100
Your seniors have retired.

1629
02:03:24.640 --> 02:03:25.979
and juniors suspended.

1630
02:03:30.004 --> 02:03:32.418
All they have to do is start talking.

1631
02:03:34.575 --> 02:03:36.175
And game over.

1632
02:03:38.593 --> 02:03:39.662
Sugar?

1633
02:03:43.419 --> 02:03:43.961
Mr. Sugga...

1634
02:03:45.845 --> 02:03:46.909
Sugar?

1635
02:04:00.595 --> 02:04:02.209
Give the phone to Bitta sir.

1636
02:04:02.742 --> 02:04:04.882
He’s not at home. You are?

1637
02:04:05.695 --> 02:04:08.640
SSP Tarn Taran. Sugga.

1638
02:04:27.694 --> 02:04:28.765
Hello...

1639
02:04:29.848 --> 02:04:31.179
Is Bitta sir back?

1640
02:04:51.035 --> 02:04:52.109
Good boy.

1641
02:05:00.162 --> 02:05:02.845
Hello. - Sir. I’ve been calling for hours.

1642
02:05:03.650 --> 02:05:07.672
But it looks like you’ve abandoned me.

1643
02:05:09.015 --> 02:05:10.360
Are you drunk?

1644
02:05:11.429 --> 02:05:12.771
Forgive me. sir...

1645
02:05:13.312 --> 02:05:16.262
... but I’m losing my mind.

1646
02:05:18.674 --> 02:05:20.552
I’ve always respected you. sir.

1647
02:05:22.433 --> 02:05:28.064
I fired in any direction you pointed me in.

1648
02:05:29.944 --> 02:05:32.894
Picked up anyone you told me to.

1649
02:05:34.778 --> 02:05:36.919
You have Delhi behind you.

1650
02:05:38.530 --> 02:05:40.677
Who do I have?

1651
02:05:42.826 --> 02:05:43.897
Sugga...

1652
02:05:44.437 --> 02:05:46.310
You’re not in your senses right now.

1653
02:05:46.580 --> 02:05:48.189
We’ll talk later.

1654
02:05:48.728 --> 02:05:50.064
I’ll handle it.

1655
02:05:50.607 --> 02:05:54.897
You keep saying you’ll ‘handle it’...

1656
02:05:57.045 --> 02:05:58.923
but nothing got handled. did it.

1657
02:06:00.000 --> 02:06:02.177
Watch your tongue. Sugga!

1658
02:06:03.269 --> 02:06:06.545
Nobody has ever talked to me this way.

1659
02:06:07.375 --> 02:06:09.004
Then do something. sir.

1660
02:06:09.827 --> 02:06:11.735
Get me transferred out of here.

1661
02:06:12.557 --> 02:06:14.193
That’s what's best for everyone.

1662
02:06:15.287 --> 02:06:16.107
Or else...

1663
02:06:17.199 --> 02:06:18.843
... everyone goes down with me.

1664
02:06:21.019 --> 02:06:22.933
Listen to me carefully...

1665
02:06:23.753 --> 02:06:26.479
and do exactly as I say.

1666
02:06:28.133 --> 02:06:29.760
I won’t let anything happen to you.

1667
02:06:40.137 --> 02:06:42.591
Hey! Nobody follows me!

1668
02:06:42.867 --> 02:06:44.502
Nobody! Move it!

1669
02:07:10.718 --> 02:07:12.085
Move... Move back.

1670
02:07:14.270 --> 02:07:16.175
We found this evidence in his pocket.

1671
02:07:17.000 --> 02:07:18.357
Looks like a suicide note.

1672
02:07:19.718 --> 02:07:21.075
Body was found in two pieces. sir.

1673
02:07:21.895 --> 02:07:25.155
Head clean off the shoulders. Was tough to recognize at first...

1674
02:07:25.431 --> 02:07:26.795
Then we identified him.

1675
02:07:38.490 --> 02:07:42.026
The Khalsa belongs to God. Victory belongs to God.

1676
02:07:43.118 --> 02:07:46.108
I am not here to grieve.

1677
02:07:46.927 --> 02:07:50.193
but to pay tribute to a brave police officer.

1678
02:07:51.012 --> 02:07:52.374
At the peak of terrorism.

1679
02:07:53.458 --> 02:07:56.994
Tarn Taran was considered to be the rocket...

1680
02:07:58.354 --> 02:08:02.434
that would blow Punjab out of this country.

1681
02:08:03.799 --> 02:08:06.515
In these circumstances. I was looking for an officer...

1682
02:08:06.793 --> 02:08:10.054
who had the courage to face the terrorists....

1683
02:08:10.876 --> 02:08:14.691
... and mount a strong campaign against them.

1684
02:08:15.231 --> 02:08:17.131
And in this situation.

1685
02:08:17.947 --> 02:08:22.844
SSP Sugga was one such officer who stepped up and took charge.

1686
02:08:23.939 --> 02:08:25.566
You call him power-hungry?

1687
02:08:26.382 --> 02:08:27.478
What power?

1688
02:08:28.287 --> 02:08:31.004
If anyone was powerful. it was the terrorists.

1689
02:08:31.561 --> 02:08:33.999
And the press was their mouthpiece.

1690
02:08:34.821 --> 02:08:37.264
and judiciary paralysed.

1691
02:08:38.083 --> 02:08:41.887
This suicide by a Sikh warrior is not an action of a coward.

1692
02:08:42.984 --> 02:08:45.698
It was not fear that drove him to death.

1693
02:08:45.975 --> 02:08:49.508
It was ingratitude and false allegations

1694
02:08:49.786 --> 02:08:51.414
made by the CBI.

1695
02:08:51.689 --> 02:08:53.046
and the human rights people...

1696
02:08:53.870 --> 02:08:56.855
which forced him to take such a drastic step.

1697
02:08:57.408 --> 02:09:00.390
The Indian state must learn to protect

1698
02:09:00.943 --> 02:09:04.746
officers like SSP Sugga. or the day isn’t far...

1699
02:09:05.290 --> 02:09:08.280
when Punjab will once again go back ten years.

1700
02:09:08.563 --> 02:09:11.549
Don’t know his name. sir. He wasn't in uniform.

1701
02:09:14.000 --> 02:09:17.471
But yes... he had green eyes.

1702
02:09:18.816 --> 02:09:19.892
Like emeralds.

1703
02:09:20.419 --> 02:09:22.021
Thank you. Jai Hind!

1704
02:09:27.903 --> 02:09:29.238
You know Kehar Singh?

1705
02:09:31.117 --> 02:09:32.181
And Jaswant Singh?

1706
02:09:37.801 --> 02:09:39.940
You'd bring him food at Kang police station. right?

1707
02:09:47.158 --> 02:09:47.957
Yes...

1708
02:09:51.971 --> 02:09:54.648
Sugga sir put me on guard duty.

1709
02:09:55.983 --> 02:09:56.520
But...

1710
02:09:58.658 --> 02:09:59.996
only for a few days.

1711
02:10:05.344 --> 02:10:06.140
Sir...

1712
02:10:07.483 --> 02:10:11.228
I’m not lying. I’m just an ordinary SPO.

1713
02:10:12.297 --> 02:10:14.161
My job isn’t even permanent yet.

1714
02:10:20.320 --> 02:10:21.649
Become a government witness.

1715
02:10:21.922 --> 02:10:23.520
We’ll make you permanent.

1716
02:10:35.557 --> 02:10:37.962
All five of these cops know that you know everything.

1717
02:10:40.372 --> 02:10:42.506
If they find out tomorrow that you're here...

1718
02:10:43.311 --> 02:10:44.380
... with us.

1719
02:10:47.056 --> 02:10:48.123
What do you think?

1720
02:10:50.532 --> 02:10:51.866
They’ll spare you?

1721
02:11:00.158 --> 02:11:00.955
Kuljit...

1722
02:11:02.568 --> 02:11:04.442
Where were you on the night of 6th September?

1723
02:11:08.711 --> 02:11:09.785
Kang police station.

1724
02:11:11.659 --> 02:11:12.993
I was on guard duty.

1725
02:11:13.113 --> 02:11:14.445
Who were you guarding?

1726
02:11:16.470 --> 02:11:18.334
It was... some...

1727
02:11:18.885 --> 02:11:19.672
Some Kehar Singh.

1728
02:11:21.812 --> 02:11:24.223
They held him there for two days. then released him.

1729
02:11:25.023 --> 02:11:25.827
And?

1730
02:11:27.972 --> 02:11:28.764
Who else was there?

1731
02:11:30.377 --> 02:11:31.441
Kuljit...

1732
02:11:34.384 --> 02:11:35.720
Who else was there?

1733
02:11:36.257 --> 02:11:38.926
No one else. Just Kehar Singh.

1734
02:11:42.404 --> 02:11:44.820
Kuljit. that night at Kang police station.

1735
02:11:44.940 --> 02:11:47.871
was Jaswant Singh kept in Kehar Singh's neighbouring cell or not?

1736
02:11:52.300 --> 02:11:53.099
He wasn't.

1737
02:11:53.912 --> 02:11:56.042
All the other cells were empty. You...

1738
02:11:56.312 --> 02:11:57.912
You can check the register.

1739
02:11:58.451 --> 02:12:00.051
There’s no entry by this name.

1740
02:12:00.586 --> 02:12:01.922
There was no one else there?

1741
02:12:05.131 --> 02:12:06.473
The CBI...

1742
02:12:07.008 --> 02:12:10.489
has registered your written statement in court. in which it is clearly written that...

1743
02:12:11.016 --> 02:12:13.691
you saw Jaswant Singh at Kang police station that night.

1744
02:12:15.292 --> 02:12:17.165
No. not there. the question came from here. look here.

1745
02:12:17.707 --> 02:12:19.039
Did you see him or not?

1746
02:12:22.514 --> 02:12:25.190
I... - Did you see him or not?

1747
02:12:25.998 --> 02:12:27.592
Yes or no? Did you see him or not?

1748
02:12:28.400 --> 02:12:29.466
Sir they gave me money.

1749
02:12:30.542 --> 02:12:32.143
To speak against the police.

1750
02:12:32.677 --> 02:12:34.284
I don’t know any Jaswant Singh.

1751
02:12:34.549 --> 02:12:35.617
He's lying!

1752
02:12:35.888 --> 02:12:36.952
Please be quiet. - He's lying!

1753
02:12:37.072 --> 02:12:38.941
Quiet! Please sit down!

1754
02:12:39.361 --> 02:12:40.960
Make him sit.

1755
02:12:47.383 --> 02:12:48.451
Who gave you money?

1756
02:12:53.000 --> 02:12:53.778
Kuljit...

1757
02:12:54.310 --> 02:12:55.086
Don’t be afraid.

1758
02:12:55.610 --> 02:12:56.917
Who gave you the money?

1759
02:13:05.540 --> 02:13:06.852
Have you lost it? What is this rubbish?

1760
02:13:07.371 --> 02:13:09.725
Why're you lying? Who's putting pressure on you?

1761
02:13:10.250 --> 02:13:11.552
Who is pressuring you? - Calm down.

1762
02:13:11.672 --> 02:13:12.718
Sit down... - Calm down.

1763
02:13:12.861 --> 02:13:13.908
Calm down - Why are you lying?

1764
02:13:14.028 --> 02:13:15.589
Who has pressured you? - Calm down

1765
02:13:16.257 --> 02:13:17.302
Be silent... - Why are you lying?

1766
02:13:17.422 --> 02:13:18.207
Cool down Samudra.

1767
02:13:18.327 --> 02:13:19.636
Maintain order in this court.

1768
02:13:19.756 --> 02:13:22.628
Your honour. his wife is sitting there. he keeps looking at her.

1769
02:13:22.748 --> 02:13:25.104
Sit down. - He's been pressured. your honour.

1770
02:13:25.224 --> 02:13:27.055
I will not have any disorder in my court room.

1771
02:13:27.175 --> 02:13:29.780
Why the hell are you lying? - Samudra...

1772
02:13:29.900 --> 02:13:30.940
You will not get away with this.

1773
02:13:32.196 --> 02:13:33.505
Thie hearing is adjourned.

1774
02:13:34.027 --> 02:13:35.600
It will resume after the recess.

1775
02:13:45.000 --> 02:13:47.158
How did you let a witness make such a fool out of you?

1776
02:13:47.962 --> 02:13:49.305
And then you attacked him in court.

1777
02:13:49.572 --> 02:13:50.917
Have you completely lost it?

1778
02:13:54.416 --> 02:13:55.491
We've lost it. sir.

1779
02:13:58.717 --> 02:14:00.060
Bitta was absolutely right.

1780
02:14:01.676 --> 02:14:02.749
This is a war and...

1781
02:14:05.708 --> 02:14:06.513
We've lost it.

1782
02:14:07.049 --> 02:14:09.470
Samudra. once again you’re taking all of this too personally.

1783
02:14:11.620 --> 02:14:12.966
So I’ve made a decision.

1784
02:14:14.051 --> 02:14:14.848
Take a break.

1785
02:14:16.193 --> 02:14:17.539
Let someone else take over this case.

1786
02:15:11.579 --> 02:15:12.652
Kuljit.

1787
02:15:33.365 --> 02:15:34.432
Recognise me?

1788
02:15:41.427 --> 02:15:43.845
I’ve come straight from the river.

1789
02:15:46.276 --> 02:15:47.339
To meet you.

1790
02:15:52.720 --> 02:15:54.329
I’m not alone there.

1791
02:15:58.640 --> 02:15:59.977
There are many like me.

1792
02:16:01.324 --> 02:16:02.128
Children.

1793
02:16:03.472 --> 02:16:04.551
women.

1794
02:16:05.356 --> 02:16:06.159
the old.

1795
02:16:10.202 --> 02:16:11.541
They will come.

1796
02:16:14.227 --> 02:16:15.839
One by one. they will all come.

1797
02:16:33.860 --> 02:16:34.931
In the winter.

1798
02:16:37.896 --> 02:16:43.269
when the water freezes at night. Kuljit...

1799
02:16:45.159 --> 02:16:47.299
it gets really cold.

1800
02:16:53.216 --> 02:16:54.557
On the outside...

1801
02:17:01.827 --> 02:17:03.157
and on the inside.

1802
02:17:05.044 --> 02:17:06.657
It’s an open wound.

1803
02:17:07.466 --> 02:17:09.883
So the water rushes in.

1804
02:17:14.991 --> 02:17:16.065
Look.

1805
02:17:27.363 --> 02:17:28.971
Water rushes in. Kuljit.

1806
02:18:20.601 --> 02:18:21.942
Why should I trust you this time?

1807
02:18:23.826 --> 02:18:25.172
I got scared last time.

1808
02:18:28.669 --> 02:18:29.202
Of what?

1809
02:18:34.053 --> 02:18:34.849
The police.

1810
02:18:37.267 --> 02:18:38.340
And this time?

1811
02:18:41.308 --> 02:18:42.374
God.

1812
02:18:47.756 --> 02:18:49.098
I don’t believe him.

1813
02:18:50.714 --> 02:18:51.515
I believe him. sir.

1814
02:18:51.787 --> 02:18:53.668
What guarantee is there that this Kuljit Singh...

1815
02:18:54.217 --> 02:18:55.548
... is telling the truth this time?

1816
02:18:57.166 --> 02:18:59.315
He’s already turned hostile in court once.

1817
02:19:00.391 --> 02:19:01.742
No guarantee. sir.

1818
02:19:02.814 --> 02:19:04.688
But my gut tells me he’s telling the truth.

1819
02:19:05.503 --> 02:19:08.456
Your gut has been wrong before. Samudra.

1820
02:19:10.072 --> 02:19:12.492
In any case. why are we still discussing this?

1821
02:19:13.569 --> 02:19:16.788
The court will never give you permission to present Kuljit as a witness again.

1822
02:19:18.675 --> 02:19:20.554
That’s why I’ve come to you three. sir.

1823
02:19:21.095 --> 02:19:22.437
To request special permission.

1824
02:19:26.205 --> 02:19:28.353
This is not only about Kuljit Singh sir.

1825
02:19:32.656 --> 02:19:36.429
It’s about probably the biggest genocide our country has seen post independence.

1826
02:19:38.580 --> 02:19:40.187
Look at the history of Punjab. sir.

1827
02:19:42.079 --> 02:19:45.292
Be it the river waters dispute or the Anandpur Sahib resolution.

1828
02:19:45.834 --> 02:19:47.443
or the ’84 riots.

1829
02:19:47.563 --> 02:19:49.452
insurgency. Black Thunder...

1830
02:19:49.572 --> 02:19:52.791
from President’s Rule to the CM’s assassination. and now...

1831
02:19:56.047 --> 02:19:56.860
Jaswant Singh!

1832
02:20:00.357 --> 02:20:01.964
Why is Punjab suffering?

1833
02:20:03.040 --> 02:20:05.189
This is a vicious circle of violence

1834
02:20:06.000 --> 02:20:09.760
which the powerful use for their own agendas. and it will never stop. It will go on and on

1835
02:20:09.880 --> 02:20:13.367
until we don’t step in and set an example.

1836
02:20:15.402 --> 02:20:15.931
Or...

1837
02:20:17.541 --> 02:20:19.149
we can just turn a blind eye

1838
02:20:20.775 --> 02:20:22.378
and be on the wrong side of history forever.

1839
02:20:22.498 --> 02:20:25.985
And we’ll never be able to forgive ourselves for this.

1840
02:20:29.626 --> 02:20:30.697
We are answerable here. sir.

1841
02:20:33.660 --> 02:20:36.873
We are answerable to our conscience. We are answerable to those families...

1842
02:20:37.148 --> 02:20:40.095
whose loved ones were marked ‘unclaimed’ and cremated by these people.

1843
02:20:41.179 --> 02:20:43.588
We are answerable to Jaswant Singh’s family.

1844
02:20:45.196 --> 02:20:47.614
and yes. we are answerable to Jaswant Singh.

1845
02:20:56.742 --> 02:21:00.770
Jaswant Singh! - Long live!

1846
02:21:01.040 --> 02:21:02.922
Brothers of the Unclaimed! - Long live!

1847
